title: lime salad
directions: Prepare jello.
When partly congealed, add pineapple, cheese, nuts and mayonnaise; mix well.
Pour into molds and chill until firm.

title: nina owen's lemon chess pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Add meal and eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes (until knife comes out clean).

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix all other ingredients with macaroni.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Put a can of biscuits on top and bake at 400° until biscuits are done.

title: cracker snackers
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a bowl; add crackers, tossing well.
Drizzle oil over cracker mixture; stir well. Place mixture in a large paper or plastic bag.
Let stand 2 hours, shaking bag occasionally.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes 11 1/2 cups.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Mash.
Mix other dry ingredients, then add water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add broccoli.

title: blueberry coffeecake
directions: Lightly grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift 3 cups flour with baking powder, soda and salt; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine brown sugar with 1 tablespoon flour and cinnamon; mix well.
Mix at medium speed in a large bowl.
Beat butter, granulated sugar and vanilla until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture (in 3 additions) alternately with sour cream (in 2 additions), beating until combined.
Turn 1/3 of batter into prepared pan, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle with half the blueberries and half the brown sugar mixture.
Repeat layering of remaining batter, blueberries and brown sugar mixture.
Bake 60 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 20 minutes.
Gently remove from pan. Mix confectioners sugar and milk until smooth; drizzle over cake when cooled.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix water and salt in bowl.
Stir yeast into box of cake mix. Then add to water.
Add flour.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise 2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Fill muffin tins 1/2 full and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 450°. Makes 18 muffins.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Mix and boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Let cool.
Arrange fresh strawberries in baked pie shell.
Pour filling over strawberries. Chill and cover with Cool Whip.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together and form into ball.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: The last 3 ingredients are to be mixed and sprinkled over batter.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, and salt together.
Cut or rub in fat until well blended.
Slowly mix in milk, using just enough to make dough that is soft but not sticky.
Turn dough onto a floured board and knead a few strokes.
Roll or pat to 3/4 inch thickness. Cut with a biscuit cutter or cut into squares with a knife. Place on a baking sheet and bake at 450° about 15 minutes. Yields:
about 16 2-inch biscuits.

title: lemon refrigerator cake
directions: Beat together first three ingredients, then bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Let cool.
Beat milk until thick (10 to 15 minutes).
Fold into first mixture.
Form graham cracker crumbs into crust in pie plate.
Fill with combined mixtures.
Top with a few graham crumbs.

title: egg pancakes
directions: Beat the eggs, then add the flour and salt.
Batter will be thick.
Add the milk slowly, mixing well to avoid lumps.
Add butter.
Melt shortening in electric frying pan.
Pour 3/4 cup batter to cover bottom of pan.
Cut into 4 pieces and turn.
Good with syrup, powdered sugar, blueberry syrup, etc.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Beat in eggs until fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in oats, chocolate chips and nuts, if used.
Drop on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: Use 8-inch square pan.
Spread 1/2 cup evenly on bottom of pan; set aside.
In a large saucepan, combine marshmallow cream, sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt.
Bring to full boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add butterscotch flavored morsels.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is well blended.
Stir in orange extract and orange rind.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup chopped nuts on top.
Chill in refrigerator until firm (about 2 hours).

title: white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl; blend well. Press onto bottom and 2 inches up sides of a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: chicken nut
directions: For open face sandwiches, decorate with small pieces of parsley and pimento or pecan half.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and take off bones.
Melt margarine and mix with dressing.
Put half in bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish, then put chicken.
Mix soups and stock; pour over chicken.
Top with rest of dressing mix.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until hot through.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine eggs, oil and mashed bananas; add to dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Bake in greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan for 60 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate, and serve with crackers.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix milk and pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan whole graham crackers.
Pour one half the pudding mix on crackers.
Add another layer of whole crackers.
Add remaining pudding.
Top with crackers and frost with your favorite pudding. Put in refrigerator at least overnight.

title: quick barbecue beef bake
directions: Cook ground beef and 1/2 cup of onion; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce.
Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan or baking dish; sprinkle with cheese.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour water over dates and let stand while preparing other ingredients.
Beat egg until light, adding sugar gradually. Sift together dry ingredients; add nuts.
Add chopped dates and flour mixture alternately to the egg mixture.
Stir in shortening and vanilla.
Pour into greased 10 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: filet de bouef
directions: Heat heavy skillet over medium-high heat.
Add 2 tablespoons of butter to pan and then the filets.
Cook until medium rare; set aside in a warm place.
Add mushrooms and saute until limp.
Set aside and keep warm.

title: sunday french toast
directions: Arrange bread in a single layer on 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs, milk, orange juice, sugar, vanilla and salt with electric beater.
Pour over slices to coat evenly.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.

title: chocolate italian cream cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening at medium speed until fluffy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, baking soda and cocoa; add to cream mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in pecans, coconut and vanilla.
Beat egg whites at high speed until stiff peaks form; fold into batter.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Spread Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: chicken and cheese enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine the chicken, 1/2 cup of the salsa and the lime juice.
to the remaining salsa, add the beef broth and tomato paste; stir until blended.

Pour half of the sauce into an 8-inch square baking pan or casserole. Spoon 1/4 of the chicken mixture into the center of each tortilla. Sprinkle 1 1/2 tablespoons of the cheese over the chicken mixture.
Loosely roll the tortillas and arrange, seam side down, over the sauce in the pan.
Spoon the remaining sauce over the enchiladas.
Sprinkle with the remaining cheese and the red onion. Bake until hot and bubbly, about 25 minutes.

title: quick cream puffs
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix well with cream cheese and Cool Whip. Cut tops off puffs (break easily) with sharp knife.
Stuff with mixture and replace tops.

title: wieners in sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish. Stir to coat wieners.
Cover and bake.
Recipe yields 30 to 40 wieners.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine sugar, marshmallows and sifted flour.
Bring to a boil, margarine, cocoa and Coca-Cola.
Pour this over first mixture until marshmallows are partly melted. Add buttermilk with 1 teaspoon soda dissolved in and eggs (well beaten).
Add to rest. Bake in 8 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch pan at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dressing mix to smooth consistency.
Set aside.
Roll out Crescent Rolls on a 9x13 cookie sheet.
Follow directions for baking.
Bake until light brown. Cool completely.
Spread cheese mix on crust.
Top with vegetables. Sprinkle with cheddar cheese.
Recommended vegetables:
Shredded carrots, peppers, cauliflower, broccoli, mushrooms, red cabbage, radishes.

title: ze jezebel sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.
It is good with ham or can be used with cream cheese on Ritz crackers.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, stir meat until browned.
Blend in onion soup mix, flour and tomato paste.
Stir in water.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Cook the noodles; place noodles in a baking dish.
Pour the beef mix over noodles and mix.
Top with bread crumbs; sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: ban-ket
directions: Mix flour and margarine, then add water.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: kernes' sirloin steak
directions: Slice steak into 3 x 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Brown both sides. Add 3 cups water and beef cubes.
Saute mushrooms.
Add to meat. Simmer on low for about 1 hour.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Boil water and margarine; add flour and beat.
Add eggs 1 at a time and beat.
Bake on a greased 13 x 9 at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Soften cream cheese and mix instant pudding and milk.
Beat all together; pour onto crust.
Top with Cool Whip. Drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is gone.
Add applesauce, eggs, liquid sweetener and oil; mix well.
Mix together, then blend in soda, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating until light.
Add flour and flavoring; beat thoroughly. Bake in a loaf pan for 1 hour at 300° to 325°.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Cut off wing tips; cut each wing in half.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour over wings and let stand, covered, in refrigerator for several hours.
Place in shallow baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° until brown.
Baste during cooking 1 1/2 hours or until done (being careful not to brown).

title: crock-pot barbecue pork ribs
directions: Wash, dry and season ribs.
Put in broiler pan under broiler for about 15 minutes on each side to brown.
Pour bottle of sauce in crock-pot.
Place ribs in pot.
Set on low heat for 6 to 8 hours, overnight or when you leave for work, they will be tender and ready when you get home.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, sharp Cheddar cheese, vinegar, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Roll into 2 small balls or 1 large ball. Cover with chopped pecans and parsley leaves.
Refrigerate.

title: challah  bread
directions: Combine yeast and water in a large mixing bowl, stirring until dissolved.
Add the sugar, oil, salt and eggs.
Using a wooden spoon, beat in 3 cups flour to make a smooth batter.
Gradually add enough flour to make a soft, workable dough that pulls away from sides of the bowl.
Turn out onto a large, lightly floured surface and knead 8 to 10 minutes, adding more flour as needed.

title: fried frog legs
directions: Scald frog legs for 3 minutes in boiling water containing 1/2 cup lemon juice and salt.
Remove; dry with clean towel.
Season with Creole seasoning or salt and pepper.
Dip in a batter made of 2 well beaten eggs, then roll in bread crumbs.
Cover frog legs well; drop into oil heated to boiling point.
Fry to a golden brown.
Remove from oil; drain well on absorbent paper.
Fry parsley for 1 minute.
Place a folded white napkin in a dish.
Lay frog legs upon it; garnish with fried parsley and sliced lemons.

title: low-carb stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Clean mushrooms.
Remove stems and using a paring knife, make the hole for stuffing larger. Brown and drain sausage.
Stir in cream cheese until melted. Spoon mixture into mushroom caps.
Bake for 20 - 25 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix together soup, broth and eggs; pour over chicken.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg yolks.
Mix well; add bananas and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites until very light.
Fold in batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bittersweet chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Line 9-inch pan with waxed paper.
Butter sides and paper; dust with flour.
Melt chocolate in double boiler over simmering water, stirring until smooth.
Cool slightly. Whisk yolks and sugar in bowl until pale yellow.
Beat whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour batter in pan.
Bake about 25 minutes until toothpick comes out with only a few moist crumbs.
Cool completely.
Run knife around side.
Turn onto platter and cool.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt oleo, marshmallows and oil.
Mix with popcorn mixture and put in a greased tube pan.
Remove from pan when set.

title: company chicken
directions: Place boneless chicken breasts in casserole (size of pan depends on how much you want to make).
Place 1/2 slice Swiss cheese on each breast.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to directions.
Place at least 2 tablespoons on each breast.
Mix jar of gravy or soup with white wine and pour over the chicken and stuffing.
Bake 1 1/4 hours or until done in a 350° oven.

title: prairie fire
directions: Drain beans, reserving 2/3 cup of the liquid.
Mash beans.
In a large skillet, combine beans, liquid, butter, cheese, peppers, onion, garlic and salt.
Heat and stir until mixture is hot and cheese melts.
Transfer to chafing dish or crock-pot.
Serve with chips.

title: russian tea
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Store in airtight container. Serve 2 teaspoons to 1 cup of boiling water.

title: butterscotch apple cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Mix together eggs, sugar and oil.
Add
dry ingredients, apples and nuts.
Blend well. Pour into
greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch morsels on top.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: turtle sauce picante
directions: Melt butter in a large pot.
Add onion, bell pepper, garlic, celery and green onions.
Stir constantly until all seasoning is wilted, about 20 minutes.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, tomato paste and 2 cans of water.
Over low heat, let cook 40 minutes.
You can also add sausage.
Put all dry ingredients into tomato gravy.
Add the turtle and cover.
Do not stir again until ready to serve.
Let cook 1 1/2 hours on low heat.
Serves about 8 people.
Serve over rice.

title: eggplant melanzane parmigiana
directions: Peel eggplant and slice.
Prepare batter by mixing egg, flour and milk.
Dip eggplant in batter. Fry in oil until brown. Drain well.

title: cottage cheese special
directions: Drain mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks.

title: japanese chicken salad
directions: Mix together chicken, sesame seed, almonds, cabbage, noodles, onions and water chestnuts.
Mix well.
Mix together oil, "Oodles of Noodles" seasoning, salt, pepper, vinegar and sugar.
Mix well and pour over salad.
Marinate overnight.
It gets better after 2 to 3 days.
Serve with soy sauce.

title: five in one cookie
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add vanilla and salt.
Sift cake flour and baking powder into creamed mixture. Divide dough into 5 parts so you can have different cookies.
Roll each part, wrap in waxed paper and chill.
When firm, slice 1/16 inch.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: hot bean compote(serves 10)
directions: Brown bacon until crisp.
Cool grease.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper; add to grease.
Stir in vinegar.
Stir over heat to thicken (bring to a boil).
Add beans and onion.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or put in a crock-pot to keep warm.
Crumble bacon on top.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown
meat
with onion; drain.
Add chilies, soups and milk. Salt
and pepper to taste.	Let simmer about 5 minutes. Dip tortillas
in
hot oil.
Layer mixture, cheese and tortillas, ending with cheese.
Put a little black pepper on top for looks. Bake
at
350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling around all edges and cheese is melted.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: overnight potatoes
directions: Melt Velveeta and margarine with half and half in microwave. Pour over potatoes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Soak overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: best cole slaw
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into a ball and roll in finely chopped pecans.
Serve with Sociable crackers.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In the pan in which the soup is to be made, put the turnips, carrots, onion, celery and butter.
Stir and cook on the surface burner until the vegetables are browned.
Now add the remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook in oven at 275° for 3 hours or at 250° for 4 to 5 hours.
Serve hot.

title: chicken cordon bleu(from minute-rice-ipes club)
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add chicken and ham; cook and stir until chicken is browned.
Stir in soup, water, green beans and mustard; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and top with cheese; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix well together.
Spread in a greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, reserving drippings. Saute onion, green pepper and celery in drippings. Combine sausage, sauted vegetables, long grain and wild rice mix (including seasoning packet), soups, cheese and mushrooms. Spoon into a shallow 2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: fat-free banana crunch muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray regular size muffin pans with nonstick cooking spray.
In a medium bowl, mix first 6 ingredients.
In a large bowl with wire whisk or fork, mix bananas, yogurt, egg substitute and vanilla extract.
Stir in flour mixture just until moistened.
Spoon batter into muffin pan cups and bake 30 minutes.

title: mansion barbecue sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.

title: stove top meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 can soup with next 6 ingredients.
Shape firmly into 2 loaves.
In skillet, brown on both sides in shortening.
Cover; cook over low heat for 25 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Top with remaining soup, water and horseradish.
Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: oatmeal refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly. Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to previous ingredients and mix.
Plump raisins in boiling water.
Drain and discard water. Add raisins to mixture and add all remaining ingredients.
Stir. Shape into a long roll on wax paper.
Wrap and chill several hours or overnight.
Slice.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen 3-inch cookies.
Ice while warm.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut out stem ends of tomatoes.
Slice 1/2 inch thick.
Combine meal, salt, sugar and pepper on waxed paper.
Coat both sides of tomato slices with mixture.
Heat shortening in skillet or in electric skillet on medium-high.
Place single layer of tomato slices in skillet.
Brown each side lightly.
Cook only until tender.
Serve immediately.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together; makes approximately 90 small meatballs.
Do not brown meatballs first.
Simmer in following sauce for 1 hour.

title: lemon salad
directions: Cook pudding according to package.
Cool.
Cook jello using only 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Cool.
Can add 1 teaspoon Knox gelatine with dry jello before adding hot water. When pudding and jello are cooled, whip cream until peaks form. Mix pudding and jello together.
Then fold in whipped cream until well mixed. Crushed pineapple can be added.
Can also be put in a jello mold. Any flavor jello and pudding can be used.

title: best brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add ingredients in the order given in the pan.
Bake at 375° for 22 minutes.

title: ground turkey meatballs
directions: Pour egg over bread crumbs.
Add tomato sauce, pepper, thyme, rosemary and vegetables.
Mix in ground turkey and form into meatballs; brown slightly.
Place in casserole and add more tomato sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: m&m's ice cream
directions: Mix well and freeze.

title: good 'n quick barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients into saucepan; bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer until thickened.

title: mexican or chinese supreme(you choose!)
directions: Measurements for this recipe depend on taste and the number of people to be served.

title: frozen crab sticks and asparagus tips
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low flame.
Add flour and salt. Stir until all flour is mixed with butter.
Add milk and stir until thickened.
Add cheese until melted.
Add crab sticks.
Cut into 3 pieces.
Add asparagus.
Make certain crab meat and asparagus are heated.
Serve over toast.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together butter or margarine and 1 cup sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Blend well.
Stir in sour cream.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir dry ingredients into butter mixture and beat until smooth.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts.
Pour about 1/3 of batter into well-greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of nut mixture and add another 1/3 of batter and 1/3 of nut mixture and then the remaining batter and nut mixture.
With spatula, swish lightly through top of cake to mix nut mixture into top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.

title: baked meatballs
directions: In large mixing bowl combine all ingredients, except Magic Sauce.
Shape meat mixture into 1-inch balls and arrange in baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven about 45 minutes or until done. Spoon off excess fat.
Pour Magic Sauce over meat.
Good either hot or cold.

title: crock-pot rump roast
directions: Rinse roast and pat dry. Sprinkle the onion soup mix in the bottom of crock-pot. Add roast. Spoon cranberry sauce over and around roast. Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours. Remove roast while thickening gravy. Turn on high. Blend soft butter and flour into a paste and whisk into gravy. Cover and cook 10 minutes on high until thick. Slice roast into 1/4-inch slices and serve with gravy. Slices can be frozen in gravy in plastic freezer bags.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together ahead of time.
Cut hole around top of 1 round loaf pumpernickel bread.
Pull top off and make several small pieces.
Pull inside out and do the same. Leave a small amount of bread around inside of loaf.
Fill with dip just before serving.

title: lime pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers into 1/4-inch slices.
Dissolve 2 cups lime in 2 gallons water; soak for 24 hours.
Drain and wash 3 times.
Soak in cold water 3 hours.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add sugar gradually until all is mixed well.
Beat in eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift salt, baking powder,
flour and cocoa.
Mix alternately with milk to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper in skillet. Drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, ketchup and black pepper; heat. Alternate meat mixture and cheese slices in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Note:
One cup sour cream mixed with 1/2 cup milk may be used instead of buttermilk.

title: spaghetti soup
directions: Bring sauce, garlic, and broth to boil; add spaghetti; reduce to low heat, cover and simmer 10-12 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Stir in remaining ingredients and cook 1 more minute.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Cook sausage, stirring to crumble.
Drain on paper towel.
Set aside.
Combine oleo and flour in saucepan.
Cook until bubbly. Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Add sausage, salt, pepper and corn; stir well.
Place half of egg slices in bottom of greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with sausage mixture and remaining egg slices and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugars, peanut butter and butter with mixer until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Then add flour, soda and salt. Mix until flour is moistened; mixture will be somewhat thick like dough.
Roll into small balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese pies
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Bake pie shells as directed.
Fill mix in pies after they have cooled.
Place in refrigerator until ready for use.
Top with berries.
Makes 2 pies.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese.
Stir until mixture is thoroughly combined.
Cool. Fold in apples, nuts, celery and Cool Whip.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
I use Red Delicious apples.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix nuts and fruits.
Cover with flour until well coated. Pour Eagle Brand on and stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° until light brown on bottom.

title: hot bacon roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Fry bacon until crisp and crumble on paper towels.
Sprinkle crescent rolls with cheese and bacon. Roll up dough starting with the wide end.
Put on baking pan, point side down.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: deep fried dandelions
directions: Pick about 2 dozen dandelion heads.
(Note:
Because the stems are poisonous, make sure that all of the stem is plucked off, but leave the green leaves.)
Mix egg and milk in a bowl.
Dump corn bread mix into another bowl.
Dip dandelions into the egg mixture, two at a time, then put them into the corn bread mix, one at a time.
When done, deep fry them on medium heat.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: 1. Mix cottage cheese, parmesan cheese, margarine, eggs, and seasonings in a large dish.
2. Grease a 9 x 13 pan and layer noodles, cottage cheese
mixture, mozzarella, and spinach. Repeat layers.
Mozzarella cheese should be the last layer. 3. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Allow to cool for 15
minutes before cutting.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato chips, and pour in a greased 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Top with chips.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chocolate chip peanut cookies
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Combine the flour, soda and salt. Cream the peanut butter and butter.
Beat in the sugars and then the vanilla and egg.
Beat in the flour mixture.
Stir in the chocolate chips.
Spoon the dough by rounded tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheets and flatten slightly.
Bake until the edges of the cookies start to turn brown and the kitchen fills with the smell of homemade cookies, approximately 8 to 10 minutes. Check at 9 minutes.

title: swedish butter ball cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Mix flour and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.
Cool and repowder.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Mix yeast and warm water.
Mix dry ingredients (salt, brown sugar and white and wheat flours).
Mix lukewarm water and margarine.
Mix yeast-water and margarine.
Add flour and sugar mixed, a little at a time, until all is mixed.
Put into greased bowl.
Cover and let rise.
Knead and form into loaves.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cover with foil last 30 minutes.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Put dry ingredients together in one bowl.
Cream sugar and shortening in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Next add flour and sour cream alternately.
Put in refrigerator for 2 hours. Roll out on floured board and cut with cookie cutter (cut bottom thicker than your top for raisin filled cookies).
Cut thick and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
The secret to keeping them soft is baking them at a high temperature and cutting them thick.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen raisin filled.
Makes 6 dozen sugar cookies.

title: chili bean soup
directions: Brown ground beef over medium heat
in large saucepan. Add salt, onions, parsley, and garlic,

stirring until onions are tender. Add beef broth, beans, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt, and hot sauce. Stir well, bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to low. Cover and simmer for at least 2 hours. Stir often to keep from sticking.

title: slimmed down pumpkin pie
directions: Brush bottom of crust with a little of the egg whites before adding them to the filling.
Mix pumpkin with honey and spices. Beat egg whites; add milk and stir into pumpkin.
Pour filling into pie shell and bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: cheese apples
directions: Mix together the margarine, sugar, cheese and flour.
Spread on top of the fruit.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pistachio torte
directions: Mix flour, sugar, margarine and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake crust at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: grand marnier
directions: Brunches conjure up pictures of a relaxed atmosphere and informality.

Men, as a rule, seem to relish the idea, especially if it is preceded by a bracer such as a Bloody Mary or a Mimosa. For a small intimate group, guests may be seated in the dining room, but for a larger group, buffets are more in tune.
Keeping in key with the informality, centerpieces should be bright and cheerful and something appropriate for the occasion.

title: potato-pepperoni supper
directions: Spray skillet with Pam.
Melt margarine in pan.
Arrange potatoes and onions in bottom of skillet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 20 minutes or until potatoes are lightly browned and tender.
Sprinkle with 1/2 can of tomato sauce.
Next sprinkle with 1/2 cheese.
Add all of pepperoni.
Add remaining sauce.
Add all remaining cheese.
Cover and cook until the casserole is heated through and the cheese is melted.

title: fudge icing
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Double the recipe for a 2 layer cake.

title: party rye pizza
directions: Brown and drain all meats.
Add Velveeta cheese to meat mixture in skillet.
After cheese melts add rest of ingredients. Spread mixture on party rye squares and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Mixture can be frozen.

title: hawaiian bread dip
directions: Blend together and let stand overnight.
Serve inside of hollowed out Hawaiian bread loaf.
Use the torn up pieces of bread for the dip.
Delicious on crackers, too!

title: grandma's oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; add margarine.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in eggs, vanilla and sugars.
Add dry mix. Bake at 350° in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes.
When it comes out of the oven, sprinkle with a mixture of cinnamon and sugar (1/2 cup white sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon). This is a very moist cake so a toothpick test won't work.

title: rhubarb surprise pie
directions: Place rhubarb into pie shell.
Sprinkle gelatin over it. Sprinkle remaining mixed ingredients over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cranberry-nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch loaf pan.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Make a well in center and pour in orange juice, eggs and melted butter; mix well. Fold in chopped nuts, cranberries and orange rind.
Pour batter in prepared loaf pan and set on middle rack in oven.
Bake 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Good toasted with butter or cream cheese.

title: green salad
directions: Wash, drain and
chill	salad
greens.	Tear
into bite size pieces.
Arrange with oranges in salad bowl.
Pour enough Sweet and Sour Dressing over greens to moisten.
Toss lightly. Garnish with additional orange sections and watercress.
Serve immediately.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer 1 hour.
Yields about 3 quarts.

title: dill crackers
directions: Mix together and pour over crackers.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: autumn stuffed squash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter and brush on cut surfaces of squash.
Place cut side down in a large baking dish without crowding.
Add enough water to cover bottom of pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
In a medium skillet, melt remaining butter over medium heat.
Saute remaining ingredients 5 minutes only stirring frequently.
Spoon vegetables into squash halves.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until squash is tender.
Serve 4.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Let the margarine soften so it will mix better.

title: tomato and cheese macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until barely done. Drain and set aside.
In large skillet, saute chopped onion in 3 tablespoons butter.
Add the tomatoes with liquid, oregano, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over medium heat about 10 minutes, breaking up tomatoes.
Add cooked macaroni, sour cream and Cheddar.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish and top with 2 tablespoons butter and Parmesan cheese.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: tom's favorite frosting
directions: Blend milk and flour in saucepan.
Cook slowly to thick paste, stirring constantly.
Cool to lukewarm.
Cream shortening, granulated sugar and salt.
Add the paste by spoonfuls, then beat until smooth and fluffy.
Fold in vanilla.
Add confectioners sugar 1/2 cup at a time, beating long and well.
(Don't try this without an electric beater.)

Weather conditions affect the amount of sugar to bring this frosting to a peak of perfection, so after the first 1 1/2 cups, cut through mixture with a knife to test consistency. Add rest of sugar as needed, beating, beating, beating.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Spray pan or lightly grease.
Spread 1 package of rolls in pan; press to edges.
Mix other ingredients together until smooth; pour over first layer.
Put second package of rolls on top.
Bake until light golden brown at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: quick white corn chili
directions: Brown meat in large saucepan; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and sliced green onions, if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips or warm bread.

title: kahlua dessert
directions: Mix and bake cake mix according to package instructions. When cooled, break into pieces into large bowl. Prepare pudding according to directions. Add Kahlua. Pour over cake. Top with Cool Whip and then the Heath bar, crushed.

title: apple bean bake
directions: In a skillet, melt butter, add cubed apples and cook until tender.
Add brown and white sugar.
Stir and cook until sugar is melted.
Stir in cinnamon, catsup and molasses.
(Sometimes I use maple syrup.)
Add beans and mix well.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake in a 400° oven for about one hour.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt white chocolate
in
hot
water;
allow
to
cool. Cream butter and sugar
together	until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a
time,
beating
well after each addition. Add melted white chocolate and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking soda together;
add
alternately
with
buttermilk
to creamed mixture. Gently fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.	Pour in 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer
cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and 2 cups sugar; beat in eggs.
Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Blend in flour, baking soda and salt.
In separate bowl, mix 4 teaspoons sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Place 1/3 batter in greased pan.
Sprinkle mixture over batter.
Add remaining batter; sprinkle mixture over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: english muffin yummies
directions: Combine all except muffins.
Spread on muffin halves.
Cut halves into 6 wedges.
Heat under broiler until bubbly.
Serve warm.

title: potato salad
directions: Scrub 1 potato per person.
Dice with peeling on.
Rinse twice in cold water.
Boil in salted water until potatoes are tender. Set pot off heat and add a small amount of vinegar and sugar.
Stir and let sit awhile.
Drain thoroughly.
Add celery seed and bacon bits.
Lightly sprinkle with garlic powder.
Dot with pickle relish and brown mustard.
Blend together without mashing potatoes.
Add just enough mayonnaise to hold potatoes together.

title: milk chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients but chips with mixer.
Stir in chips. Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for 45 minutes at 350°. Store in refrigerator.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Layer in oblong dish:

1/2 package crumbled tortillas in bottom of dish, then layer the hamburger and onion mixture, next layer green chilies and Cheddar cheese, then layer remaining tortillas. Mix the soups and milk together and pour over all.
Cover with foil to bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in a 9 x 11 baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: teriyaki chicken(stir-fry chicken with steamed vegetables)
directions: In large frying pan, cook chicken on high in olive oil, adding soy sauce during browning process to keep from sticking. Add wine and stir in onions, pepper, and garlic salt. Continue to add soy sauce as needed for liquid.
Cook on medium high for about 2 minutes.	Add mushrooms, water chestnuts, and bell pepper.
Cook on medium high for about 4 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables over top of chicken mixture. Allow vegetables to steam until desired tenderness; 1/4 cup water may be added before vegetables if there is not enough moisture to create steam.
Can be served over rice or with Chinese noodles.
Serves 4-6.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Cook together chicken, onion and celery, until chicken is tender.
Cool slightly.
Take chicken from bones and cut into pieces.
Mix with sour cream, chicken soup and MBT. Put into baking dish.
Crush crackers and pour over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle poppy seed over crackers.
Drizzle melted margarine over all.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: angel food cake and jello
directions: Slice cake in thin slices; place in cake pan.
Slice strawberries and spread over cake; sprinkle sugar over strawberries.
Mix jello and pour over cake.
Chill until jello is set.

title: bean dip dish
directions: Place beans on bottom of baking dish; top with almonds, sour cream and grated cheese.
Microwave for 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve with chips of your choice.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Layer bread, cooked sausage and cheese. Pour egg and milk mixture over it and set in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, add 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 cup milk blended and pour over everything.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix together; pour 1/2 batter into a greased, long pan.
Mix 1 cup brown sugar and 3 tablespoons cinnamon; sprinkle cinnamon mixture over cake and swirl with a knife.
Pour rest of batter on top and make more cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: apple mallow yam bake
directions: Toss apples, pecans, sugar and cinnamon.
Alternate layers of apple mixture and yams in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot with margarine.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with marshmallows.
Broil until lightly browned.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: tuna, pasta salad
directions: Chop basil (must be sharp knife so you do not bruise herb). (If bruised, will turn salad black.)
Pat dry.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Do not rinse.
Remove seeds from tomatoes and drain very well.
Mix lime juice, salt, sugar and pepper and taste to your liking.
Right before serving, use a big bowl, add pasta, tomatoes, tuna or chicken, basil, onion and lime juice.
Mix. Serve at room temperature.

title: orange blossom punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan; heat and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil and continue cooking for 5 minutes without stirring.
Cool, then place in refrigerator to chill.
When ready to use, add juices and ginger ale; mix thoroughly and pour over ice in punch bowl.

title: orange chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl, beat egg; add orange juice.
In another bowl, combine stuffing mix, paprika, orange peel and salt.
Dip chicken into egg mixture, then into crumbs, turning to coat well. Pour butter into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken in baking dish, turning once to butter both sides.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes or until the chicken is tender and juices run clear.
Garnish with orange slices if desired.

title: holiday fruit drops
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda; set aside.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and fruit.
Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden.
Store airtight.
Can be frozen.

title: creamy vegetable cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add next 6 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine in heavy pan over low heat.
Add flour and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cheese, paprika and pepper. Stir over heat until cheese is melted, then stir cheese mixture into vegetable mixture.
Yields 8 cups.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all in one bowl, dry ingredients first.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
I double this recipe because the can of pumpkin has 2 cups.
It makes 4 small loaves.

title: hors d'oeuvres called dog food
directions: In frying pan, brown ground chuck and pork sausage and drain off all grease.
Put meat back into frying pan over medium heat and add cheese.
Stir until all is mixed and cheese is melted. Using a tablespoon, put a spoonful on top of each rye.
Put each on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until top and bottom of rye are slightly toasted.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Pour coffee over the cocoa.
Add soda to milk.
Mix together and bake in layers or in sheet pan at 350°.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Pinch up pieces big enough for meatballs and roll between hands.
(If mixture starts sticking to hands, wet them with water.)
Place in 4-quart pressure cooker.

title: special occasion chicken
directions: Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook 10 minutes. Turn chicken; add mushrooms and shallots.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Transfer chicken to platter.

title: chocolate coconut cracker snacks
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Top with crackers, side by side, in a single layer.
In microwave, melt oleo.
Stir in sugar and cook 1 minute in microwave on High.
Stir and drizzle over crackers.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet on rack.
Store in an airtight container 1 week or freezer for 1 month.
Makes 36.

title: macque choux(cajun smothered corn)
directions: Cut off tips of corn kernels into a bowl.
Scrape milk and remaining pulp from cob with a knife.
Set aside.
Combine oil and butter in a large skillet over medium heat until butter melts. Add corn, tomatoes and remaining ingredients and cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes.
Reduce heat; cover and cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar together.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Place in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli shrimp and cheese quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine milk, eggs, flour, pepper and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Set aside.
Alternately layer onion, broccoli, cheese and shrimp in pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over layers.
Place pie on cookie sheet and bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: kaduffle glades(german dumplings)
directions: Cook potatoes until just tender.
Bring a large pan of water with a pinch of salt to a boil.
Coarsely mash potatoes and grate 1 large onion into the potatoes.
Add 1 egg, pinch of salt, parsley and mix with a fork and add flour until stiff.

title: no bake peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Mix peanut butter, crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Melt chips and wax together; pour over peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: haddock fish bake
directions: Turn oven to 375°.
Place fish in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; pour soup over fish.
Bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients over fish.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Serves 6.

title: tuna noodle casserole(great for church potlucks!)
directions: Boil and drain noodles.
Drain and flake tuna with a fork. Mix all ingredients (save some cheese for the top).
Pout in a 2-quart dish.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with a little cheese just before you remove it from the oven.

title: ham-broccoli bake
directions: Take broccoli spear, wrap piece of cheese around it.
Wrap ham around cheese and secure with a toothpick.
Do this with all 8 slices.
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream with mustard.
Pour over ham, cheese and broccoli roll-ups.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: candied yams
directions: Parboil yams 15 minutes. Peel and slice lengthwise.
Arrange in a buttered baking dish.
Pour sugar over surface, dot with butter and cover with orange juice.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until sugar melts and yams are lightly browned.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and baking powder.
Combine pumpkin, oil and eggs and add pumpkin mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Mixture should be lumpy.
Do not overmix as this will cause bread to be coarse and tough.
Pour batter into two greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick put in center of loaf comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely on racks. When cool, wrap each loaf and store at room temperature.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Break up bread in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Especially good served hot as side dish with pork.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together, pour into shallow greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about one hour.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: corn dish
directions: Mix well and pour in a greased dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ruth's hamburger and cabbage
directions: Chop onions coarsely.
Melt fat in heavy kettle; toss in onion and hamburger.
Cook over high fire until meat is brown.
Stir in tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook slowly 20 minutes. Shred cabbage.
Pare and chop apple fine.
Stir cabbage, apple, lemon juice and sugar in with hamburger.
Cover and cook gently for about 40 minutes.
Serves 6 generously.

title: chicken tamale pie
directions: Preheat oven to
350°.	In bowl, combine muffin mix and cheese.
Prepare
according
to package directions; set aside. In saucepan,
stir
remaining ingredients until blended.
Heat through.
Spoon muffin mixture into greased 2-quart casserole. Spoon hot soup
mixture over muffin mixture to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Bake
minutes or until bread is golden.	Garnish with additional	cheese,
green onions and sliced cherry tomatoes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Place in refrigerator until chilled enough to form a ball.
Roll ball in nuts and parsley.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Can be made ahead of time and frozen.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Garnish with chopped nuts.

title: fresh blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except blueberries. Mix until well blended.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in blueberries. (If batter seems too thick, you can slowly add more milk until muffin consistency.)
Fill greased (or use paper) muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish (glass).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
I baked it at 300° for 1 hour and it was better.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Form into meatballs, using a rounded tablespoonful for each.
Brown well in shortening.
Drain excess fat.
Sprinkle flour over meatballs; stir gently to coat meatballs.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Beat together egg, butter and milk and add all at once to flour mixture and stir.
Stir in blueberries.
Spoon into greased 2 3/4-inch muffin cups and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased casserole.
Sprinkle top with 1 small package Fritos, crumbled.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.

Add milk to cream of mushroom soup over low heat, then the cheese until melted, then add rest of ingredients and mix well and pour into a well-greased casserole. Cover with cereal flakes or potato chips and put bits of butter on top of flakes and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes (covered).

title: pecan pralines
directions: Cook and stir until the sugar dissolves, then add pecans. Boil for 3 to 5 minutes, until soft ball forms when dropped in cold water.
Beat until thick and still shiny.
Quickly drop by the teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix the cream and marshmallows.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 hour, then add other ingredients.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients except
the crabmeat.
Melt in double
boiler or microwave.
When	thoroughly
mixed,
add crabmeat and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet pea salad
directions: Drain peas; add onion, pickle, eggs, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Serve chilled on lettuce leaf with slice of egg on top.

title: flavorful baked beans
directions: Empty 1 can beans into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Combine brown sugar and mustard; sprinkle 1/2 over beans.
Top with the other can of beans and sprinkle with remaining brown sugar mixture, chopped bacon and catsup.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: cheese apple squares
directions: Measure flour; add sugar and baking powder and stir well. Cream cheese and butter.
Add blended dry ingredients.
Mix well. Divide in half.
Press half of mixture into ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Spread with apple jelly.
Sprinkle remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: whole wheat buttermilk muffins
directions: Combine
dry
ingredients.
Combine
wet
ingredients. Fold quickly
wet
and dry together, just until flour is moistened. Spoon into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Put sugar and flour in mixing bowl. Bring to a boil the oil, oleo, water and 4 tablespoons cocoa. Pour while hot over sugar and flour. Mix well.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Add water to juice concentrate according to directions on cans.
Chill and pour over sherbet just before serving.
Serves 50 punch cup size servings.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix crab meat, cream cheese and horseradish.
Put in small baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Serve with corn chips.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Soften the butter.
Add flour and powdered sugar.
Add nuts. Work the dough with your hands.
Form a ball of 1/2 dollar size. Squeeze in fingers to indent.
Bake at 300° until light brown on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: apple cider punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Garnish punch with floating orange slices, decorated with cloves.

title: easy chicken bake
directions: Combine in a casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: field peas
directions: Bring fresh peas to boil; drain off water.
Put seasoned salt and water in peas; boil for 1 hour.

title: barbecue chicken tenders
directions: Cook on top of stove until chicken is tender.

title: mrs. jones' fruit cake
directions: Mix eggs sugar and butter.
Add in flour, soda, and salt.
Mix in fruit and nuts.
Bake in iron skillet at 250° for about 2 hours.

title: country ham muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease 12 muffin pan cups.
Prepare muffin mix according to package directions, adding the ham with dry ingredients and the maple extract with liquid ingredients.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin pan cups.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexicali crock-pot pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Add onion and garlic to beef; cook until onion is soft and clear.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Combine enchilada and tomato sauces into a bowl; drain corn and add to sauces.
Wipe inside of crock-pot with oil. Place 1 tortilla in the bottom of the crock-pot.

Make 4 layers, using 1/4 of each ingredient in this order: ground beef mixture, chili beans, corn, sauces, cheese and tortilla. End with a cheese topping. Cover crock-pot and cook on low for 5 to 7 hours.

title: mexican sausage balls
directions: Set sausage at room temperature 2 to 3 hours.
Mix all ingredients together in bowl. Shape into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans with soup and milk with 3/4 can of onions. Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cheddar salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in pineapple with juice and sugar.
Let cool.
(You may put into freezer for a short time until it starts to gel.)
Fold in remaining ingredients. Spoon into a 9-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: indian corn stew
directions: *Ground deer meat adds perfect flavor.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add to eggs, milk, oil, corn, cheese, onion and jalapeno peppers.
Mix well and bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until brown and firm in the center.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix all ingredients. Dry fish and dip in batter, then in cornmeal and fry.

title: cranberry relish mold
directions: Grind cranberries through food grinder, using coarse blade. Combine ground cranberries and sugar; set aside.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup; add enough water to reserved syrup to make 1 cup.
Add syrup
mixture to dissolved gelatin; chill until partially set.
Fold ground cranberry mixture, crushed pineapple, chopped celery and chopped walnuts into partially set gelatin.
Pour into 5-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold to serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Great with turkey at Thanksgiving!

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix starch with sugar.
Add milk and other ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Let cool, then pour over bananas and wafers.

title: busy barbecue filling
directions: Combine all ingredients, except hamburger buns, in a large pot or slow cooker.
Simmer on top of stove for 3 hours or in slow cooker on high for 8 hours.
Makes filling for 12 sandwiches.

title: meat balls with gravy
directions: Combine everything except flour in a bowl; mix well.
Roll the meat into little balls and dredge with flour.
In a skillet, brown the meat balls in oil.
Remove meat. Retain 2 tablespoons drippings.
Add flour, stirring constantly until brown.
Add milk and water, stirring until gravy thickens.
Return meat to pan and simmer slowly until meat is heated.

title: cherry dump cakegroves, texas
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350°.
Get 13 X 9 cake pan and fill the bottom with pie filling.
Then put the yellow cake mix on top of the pie filling.
Melt the butter and pour it on top of the cake mix.
Spread evenly.
Put in oven and bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: nancy's cookies
directions: Using a double boiler, melt morsels and blend with peanut butter.
Pour over cornflakes and stir well.
Drop onto cookie sheet and stick in refrigerator until firm.

title: super oyster stew
directions: Blend first four items to smooth paste and stir in oysters and their liquor.
(Flour is one secret of stew's perfection.)
Simmer oysters over very low heat until edges curl.
Pour into scalded milk by pouring into bowl of spoon to prevent splashing.
Remove pan from heat; cover and let stand 15 minutes.
(This improves flavor.)
Have tureen and soup bowls hot; add pats of butter or margarine.
Reheat stew briefly until hot and serve.
Serves 4.

title: bacon pie
directions: Mix in blender Bisquick, milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Add cooked bacon that is cut into small pieces.
Ham may be used instead of bacon if desired.
If you are a broccoli fan, this is also a tasty addition.
Cook in 400° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: tuna and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender and drain.
Mix macaroni and all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in two layers. Cool. Cut each layer into 2 layers.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in heavily greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45-60 minutes.
Makes 2 or 3 breads.

title: avgolemono soup(egg-lemon soup)
directions: Bring chicken broth to boiling point, then lower heat.
To well beaten eggs, add lemon juice.
Dilute egg and lemon juice mixture with a little hot soup, stirring constantly.
Add rest of egg-lemon mixture to broth, stirring constantly.
Bring broth to a boil; remove from heat and let stand.
Salt to taste.

title: miss birdie's pickles
directions: Put cucumbers in refrigerator hydrator with gallon of cold water and salt.
Let sit one week.
Cut board to fit hydrator to hold pickles down.
Pour off water, cover with boiling water and let stand overnight; drain.
Cut in slices.
Cover with boiling water, alum and horseradish.
Let stand overnight; drain.
Cover with boiling water and same horseradish root.
Let stand overnight again.
Bring to boil remaining ingredients and pour over pickles. Repeat for 5 mornings.
On 5th morning put in heated jars and fill with boiling liquid, then seal.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa and salt together 3 times.
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Then add eggs and mix well.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add red food coloring and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in soda dissolved in vinegar.
Beat well.
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lamb burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into patties.
Broil on grill. Serve with Yogurt Dressing.

title: cashew and tuna casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325 degrees, grease casserole dish. Mix all together put in casserole dish, put noodles on top bake uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: pep pills
directions: Mix ingredients well, except raisins.
Then add raisins and mix well.
Roll in small balls.
Keeps week refrigerated.

title: tuna orleans
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well. Pour into a quart casserole dish. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together and spread in pan.
Top with lettuce, tomato, green onion, chopped olives and cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: mandarin cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and 2/3 cup Mandarin juice.
Fold in oranges and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Cool 2 hours before icing.

title: busy day chocolate cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Punch 3 holes.
Pour vanilla, vinegar, oil and 1 cup water into holes and mix.
Blend in second cup of water.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nut cookies
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto buttered baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Heat milk, butter and sugar and cool to warm.
Add eggs and 2 cups flour to milk mixture.
Beat until smooth (12 minutes). Gradually add remaining flour, a little at a time.

title: lawn party sandwiches
directions: Heat the butter in a microwave-safe dish for 1-2 min. or until melted.
Stir in the onion, poppy seeds and mustard.
Chill, covered for 8 - 10 hours.
Remove the poppy seed mixture from the refrigerator 1 hour before needed to prepare the recipe.
Split each pkg. of rolls horizontally with a serrated knife into 2 layers, leaving the bottom layer in the pan.
Spread the cut sides or the rolls with the poppy seed mixture.
Layer the ham and cheese on the bottom layer of rolls.
Top with remaining roll layer.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 min.
For variety, add chopped red bell pepper when assembling sandwiches.
May be prepared in advance and frozen unbaked.
Bake the frozen rolls at 350 degrees until heated through.
These are great!

title: spinach quiche(microwave)
directions: Cook first three ingredients on High until onion is soft, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Combine next five ingredients in bowl and beat until well blended.
Add cheese, spinach and seasoning and mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell.
Cook on 70% power until center is barely set, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.
Total cooking time is 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal crunchies
directions: Cream honey and butter.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Stir flour and soda together and mix with creamed ingredients.
Drop on lightly greased sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields approximately 3 dozen.

title: chicken chili(makes 6 servings)
directions: Heat oil with first 4 ingredients until onion is al dente. Add chicken.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Add flour to make roux. Cook 5 minutes.
Gradually add chicken broth.
Cook and stir until smooth.
Add salt, hot sauce and chilies.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in beans and green pepper. Cook an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil. Cook ground turkey in a nonstick skillet until brown, stirring to crumble. Drain. Stir meat into vegetable mixture. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: bette's chicken with rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken and pat dry; set aside.
In oblong pan, mix rice, water, celery soup, mushroom soup and poultry seasoning.
Arrange chicken pieces on top of mixture. Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over chicken.
Cover pan with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Stew chicken together with a celery stick, a carrot and a small onion.
Take the meat from the bones and set aside.
Reserve chicken broth.
To make dumplings, cut shortening into dry ingredients and add liquid a little at a time.
Roll on floured board and cut into strips, cutting dumplings to approximately 1 x 2-inch pieces.
Drop into boiling chicken stock.
Turn heat down and cook at moderate temperature for approximately 15 minutes. Add 1/2 cup milk; turn off burner and cover.
Let set for several minutes before serving.

title: hot mulled wine
directions: Boil the sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Mix sugar water, lemon peel, cloves and cinnamon. Boil 10 minutes. Strain.
Add brandy and wine. Heat gently, but do not boil. Serve in mugs. Sprinkle with nutmeg or place cinnamon stick in each.

title: peach cream
directions: Whip the whipping cream with sugar to taste.
Cut up peaches and stir into cream.
Add gelatin, dissolved in warm water.
Place in mold to harden.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl, mixing well.
Pour into casserole.
Bake, covered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sloppy joe fondue
directions: In skillet, brown beef, stirring occasionally.
Add Sloppy Joes mix and stir to mix well.
Blend in tomato paste and water called for in package directions.
Add celery and green pepper; bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Turn into fondue saucepan and place directly over low flame.
Spear a piece of French bread (cubed with crust on one side of each piece), and dip in.
Yields 4 servings.

title: potato pancakes(european style)
directions: Peel and grind	8
medium potatoes, scrape in a dash of onion, grated.
Add
salt	and
1	tablespoon flour, grate 1/2 slice dry bread.
Beat the 3 eggs slightly and add to mixture. Fry in hot oil
until brown, 10 minutes each side.
These are delicious served with sour cream.

title: sugar cakes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheet. Sprinkle granulated sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Unfold crusts and brush each with melted butter.

Combine sugar and brown sugar. Mix well. Sprinkle over crust. Combine chocolate chips and pecans and sprinkle over crust. Press slightly so chips and pecans won't fall out when you start to roll the crescents. Cut each crust into 12 wedges (I use a pizza cutter for this). Roll each wedge starting at the wide end and rolling to the point. Place on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake for about 15 minutes or until delicately browned.
As you remove crescents from baking sheet, roll each one in confectioners sugar to coat.
I sometimes like to give them a second dusting with the sugar.
Makes 24.

title: ranch cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except nuts.
Mixture will be soft. Press nuts in as you form into ball.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.
Makes 1 very large cheese ball or two medium size balls.

title: sugar and spice pecans
directions: Beat egg white with water until frothy.
Add pecans and mix until nuts are coated.
Mix together sugar, cinnamon and salt. Add to nuts and mix.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: nutty chicken salad
directions: Toss vegetables together with nuts and chicken.
Add croutons and dressing of choice and serve.

title: famous salad
directions: Add hot water to reserved pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Pour into Jell-O powder to mix.
Add 1 cup cold water and mix thoroughly.
When Jell-O is partially hardened, beat until light. Add cream cheese, pimientos (cut fine), chopped nuts and celery (cut fine).
Add drained pineapple.
Fold in whipped cream.
Mold and let set.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix the fruit together.
Add the instant pudding.
Do not add milk to pudding.
Stir in dry.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Delicious and easy.

title: corn chowder
directions: Bring milk to boil in large saucepan.
Lower heat.
Add cream cheese and corn, stirring often, over low heat until cream cheese has melted.
Reserve.
In a small skillet, cook bacon and onion until bacon is crisp; drain off excess grease.
Add bacon, onion and potatoes to milk mixture.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; remove from bone.
Cut in bite-size pieces. Mash the can of Ro-Tel tomatoes together with half of the juice from the can.
Saut onions and bell pepper in butter.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Add pimento.
Add Ro-Tel and melted cheese. Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Drain.
Mix spaghetti and chicken. Pour other mixture over and mix well.
(Note:
May add some chicken broth to keep from being so firm.)
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: nellie's favorite chocolate cake
directions: Mix together sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and sour cream.
Mix together flour, baking soda and salt; add to mixture.
Last, add cocoa, hot water and butter.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 layers.
Very moist.

title: fruit punch
directions: When diluting juices, add only 2 cans water rather than amount specified on cans.
Pour all diluted juices, grenadine, sugar and water into large punch bowl.
Just before serving, add ginger ale, ice cubes and slices of fresh orange, lime and cherry for garnish. Serves 50.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Stir until thoroughly mixed.
If too thick, additional water can be added for desired consistency.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours until set.
Let cool before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: farmer's catfish fillets
directions: Cut fish in medium size pieces.
Salt and pepper fish.
Beat egg yolks. Mix flour and cornmeal.
Dip fish in eggs, then coat with mixture.
Drop in hot oil.
Cook over medium heat 30 minutes or until done.

title: pinto bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Add remaining ingredients and toss together well.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until you can squeeze them (about 1 hour at 350° or about 15 minutes on High in microwave).
Cut in half and spoon out the meat of the potato into a large bowl.
Add all ingredients and mash until smooth.
If needed, add small portions of milk. Fill potato skin shells with the mixture and melt in the microwave for about 5 minutes.

title: rice and mushrooms
directions: Put all ingredients into baking dish and bake.
No need to mix.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: cheese manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti according to directions.
Add salt, oregano and oil to water.
Drain but keep moist.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Cut in Crisco.
Add buttermilk.
Roll out dough adding as little flour as possible.
Bake at 500° until done.
Brush with butter.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Rub potatoes with oil, pierce with fork and bake at 400 degrees for 1 hour, 20 minutes or until tender.
Allow to cool to touch.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving a thin shell.
Place pulp in large bowl.
Saute onions in 1/4 c. butter until tender.
Add to potato pulp along with light cream, sour cream, salt & pepper.
Beat until smooth, fold in cheese, stuff potato shells and place in 13X9 pan.
Melt remaining butter, drizzle over potatoes and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350 degrees for 20-30 minutes or until heated through.

title: layer dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers and margarine.
Then layer ingredients in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or at 350° for 45 minutes.
Chill and cut.

title: fruit delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread 1 can blueberry pie filling in square pan.
Sprinkle 1 (9 ounce) package white cake mix over filling.
Pat lightly.
Dot with 1/4 cup margarine.
Cover with 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mandarin orange pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except oranges well; fold in oranges. Pour into baked pie shell or graham cracker crust.
Chill until set.

title: self-iced chocolate cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, milk, eggs, pecans and chocolate morsels.
Pour mixture into greased 10-inch microwave tube pan. Microwave at High 14 minutes; rotate pan 1/4 turn at 3-minute intervals.
Allow to stand 5 minutes.
Invert cake onto serving platter.
The chocolate morsels may be on the top and can be spread as icing while hot, if desired.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: In medium bowl, blend cream cheese, sour cream and horseradish until smooth and creamy.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and 1/2 cup dried beef.
Chill cheese mixture about 15 minutes for easier handling.
Shape cheese mixture into a ball.
Roll in remaining dried beef.
Chill at least 20 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saut onion in butter. Add broth, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper. Bring to a boil; cook 15 to 20 minutes. Ladle soup in bowl. Put slice of bread in bowl and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Grease cookie sheet.
Line with wax paper and grease. Pour batter onto cookie sheet. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle tea towel with powdered sugar. Drop out cake, peel off paper.
Roll up cake lengthwise in towel.
Cool completely.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix condensed milk, lemon juice and Dream Whip.
Layer mixture and berries alternately in pie crust.
Top with whipped cream.

title: snickerdoodle cookies(children love the name of this recipe.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix thoroughly the sugar, shortening and egg. Sift flour, cream of tartar, salt and baking soda into a bowl; mix well.
Chill dough in refrigerator.
When chilled, remove and roll into balls.

title: ham appetillas
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients except tortillas. Blend well. Put a few drops of water in a Teflon covered frypan.
Put on medium-low heat.
Place 1 tortilla in frypan. Cover and cook for 10 to 15 seconds or until it is soft enough to roll up.
Remove from pan.
Spread cream cheese mixture over.
Roll up tightly. Wrap in foil, twisting ends of foil to hold shut. Repeat process until all of the mixture is used. Refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: lemon crinkles
directions: Beat margarine with 3/4 cup of sugar until fluffy at high speed.
Beat in egg, vanilla, lemon extract and milk.
Sift in flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda, a little at a time, until blended.
Chill dough until firm.
Form into marble-sized balls (about 1 teaspoon each).
Coat balls by rolling in a mixture of remaining 1/2 cup sugar and lemon rind.
Carefully place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 8 minutes or until tops are crackled and edges lightly browned.
Cool completely on wire racks.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: crabmeat salad
directions: (Imitation crabmeat may also be used and shrimp may also be added.)

title: deviled ham snack
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften. Mix all ingredients. Serve with Club crackers or on rye bread.

title: strawberry shortcakes
directions: Mix the strawberries and 1/2 cup sugar.
Let stand 1 hour. Heat oven to 450°.

Cut shortening into flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and salt with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Stir in milk just until blended. Turn dough onto lightly floured surface. Gently smooth into a ball.
Knead 20 to 25 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured 3-inch cutter.
Place about 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Split crosswise while hot.
Spread with margarine. Fill and top with strawberries. Top with sweetened whipped cream.

title: summertime punch
directions: Steep tea in water for 10 minutes.
Remove tea bags and mix tea with remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Ginger ale may be chilled and added just before serving if more carbonated punch is desired.
Serves 15.

title: imitation crab ball
directions: Mix all together.
Chill for a few minutes; form into a ball. May be rolled in parsley or chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Mix until well blended.
Add pimiento, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire, lemon juice and seasonings.
Mix well.
Chill. Shape into a ball, roll in chopped pecans.

title: watergate salad
directions: In a large bowl, pour in drained pineapple, Cool Whip, pistachio pudding, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well. Chill before serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Add the next five ingredients and part of the cheese.
In large baking dish, put a layer of meat mixture; repeat again.
Put remainder of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Very good!
This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: beef-carrot casserole
directions: Cook 8 oz noodles.
Drain and add to above mixture.
Mix well.
In a 3 quart casserole, alternate meat mixture and cottage cheese mixture.
Beginning with noodles and ending with noodles. Top with 1 cup shredded cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for
20 minutes or until hot.

title: barkley's beef in wine sauce
directions: Melt butter, blend in flour; stir in boiling bouillon.
Add bay leaf and cloves; heat.
Simmer and set aside.

title: date pudding
directions: Place brown sugar, water and butter in pan and bring to a boil.
Mix together brown sugar, sweet milk, flour, baking powder, cinnamon, butter and dates.
Drop by teaspoon into hot liquid. Place nut meats on each spoonful of dough.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Mix and pour over pork chops.
Cook in oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to package. Prepare Minute rice to yield 3 cups cooked.
Stir all the ingredients together and pour into a lightly buttered casserole dish.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes or until browning.
Let set 5 minutes.

title: potato chowder
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Saute bacon with onion in large kettle.
Add potatoes, celery, carrots, water, bouillon and seasonings.
Cover and cook gently until vegetables are tender. Add milk and heat through.
Combine flour and butter.
Add to chowder.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until chowder thickens.

title: mincemeat
directions: Cook pork and beef until tender. Cook raisins until tender. Peel, core and slice apples. Cook.
Mix all ingredients and add sugar, vinegar and spices; cook all together for short time.
Can be used immediately or canned.
