title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles; prepare spaghetti sauce with tomato sauce, paste, spaghetti sauce mix and meat.
Combine eggs, cottage cheese and salt.
Mix well.
In greased pan, alternate layers of half each noodles, sauce, cottage cheese, Mozzarella and Parmesan. Repeat layers and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: artichoke and spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine spinach, artichokes, cream, salt, pepper and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese.
In small bowl (with a mixer at medium speed), beat cream cheese until fluffy. Reduce speed to low and gradually add milk, mixing until just blended.
Spoon the spinach mixture into shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole dish (or 8 x 8 glass baking dish).
Pour cream cheese mixture evenly over the spinach mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/3 cup Parmesan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until edges bubble and the top is golden.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery together.
Boil and chop chicken breasts.
Mix with soups and cheese.

title: scallops a la michael(an original recipe)
directions: Saute scallops in margarine and seasonings.
Cube Velveeta into large bowl with flour, mushroom soup and milk.
Heat in microwave on High for approximately 7 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Add scallops and bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: unusual cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Fold in oatmeal and Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cheddar-potato bake
directions: In 1 1/2 quart casserole, combine soup, sour cream, onion and pepper.
Stir in potatoes until blended.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Garnish with shredded cheddar cheese and sliced green onion, if desired.

title: pepper steak
directions: Marinate meat in mixture of soy sauce, garlic and 1/2 cup of beef bouillon for 15 minutes.
Drain meat, reserving liquid.
Melt a piece of fat trimmed from steak in a very hot frying pan. Quickly brown meat on each side.
Add onion, celery and green pepper and cook until tender.
Mix cornstarch with reserved liquid and remaining beef bouillon; stir into meat and vegetables.
Cook until thickened.
Serve with rice.
Tomato wedges may be added for garnish.
Serves 8.

title: patio beans
directions: Layer bacon on bottom, then 1 can kidney beans, onion, green pepper, tomatoes and other can of beans.
Spread brown sugar over; pour bottle of ketchup and put bacon on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 2 hours.
Stir after 1 hour.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased (heated hot) 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes. Reheats well.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add egg and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mix.
Add nuts. Shape into rolls about 2 1/2-inches thick (across).
Wrap in wax paper and chill thoroughly.
Slice very thin, 1/8-inch or less.

title: long john's fish batter
directions: Mix ingredients until consistent of pancake batter.
Beat egg white until frothy and fold into mixture.
Don't stir much.

title: strawberry delight(fat free spread)
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Whisk until smooth. Keep refrigerated.
Use as a spread on toast, bagels, muffins or crackers.
Can be used as a fresh fruit dip.

title: canadian apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in greased baking dish and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix flour, oats and sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles
coarse bread crumbs; sprinkle over apples. Bake
until apples are tender and topping is lightly browned
(35 to 40 minutes).
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
This is delicious
with vanilla
ice
cream
and
served
warm.
The Gravenstein apples are super to use!

title: spiced tea
directions: Bring water, cinnamon, and cloves to boil. Turn off the heat and place tea bags in the mixture. Steep for 5 minutes. Remove tea bags and cloves. Add pineapple and lemon juices, sugar and ginger ale. Makes 20 cups.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in warm water. Stir in other ingredients. Pour 1/2 of mixture into square dish and let chill until slightly firm. Cover with small carton sour cream. Cover with remaining Jell-O mixture and chill until firm. Cut into squares and serve.

title: candy bar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, powdered sugar, vanilla, Pet evaporated milk and flour.
Mix well.
Chill.
Roll out on floured surface to 12-inch rectangle.
Cut into 3 x 1 1/2-inch rectangles.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 12 to 16 minutes. When cookies are cool, mix caramels and Pet milk.
Heat until caramels melt.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in oleo, powdered sugar and pecans.
Put 1 teaspoon this filling on each cookie.
Very good!

title: three cheese whole wheat pizza
directions: The crispiest crusts are achieved by using a pizza stone.
It is worthwhile obtaining a pizza stone for this recipe and for baking many other kinds of breads.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
In a large bowl, beat together brown sugar, eggs and butter until light and frothy.
Blend in pumpkin and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and raisins. Stir just enough to moisten flour mixture.
Do not overmix.
Spoon mixture into greased 2-inch muffin pans.
Fill cups three-fourths full.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: mushrooms and chicken breasts
directions: Soak chicken slices in well beaten eggs for a few minutes, then roll each slice in bread crumbs.
You can either fry or broil the chicken in the butter until light golden brown.
Place in pan; cover each piece of chicken with mushroom slices and cheese.
Add wine and/or broth.
Squeeze lemon juice over lightly.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: banana chocolate pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk in saucepan.
Stir and cook over medium heat until boils.
Remove from heat.
Pour in bowl.
Place wax paper on surface of hot pudding (to prevent a surface film). Chill.
Line bottom of 1-quart casserole dish with wafer.
Stop with bananas.
Cover with layer of chocolate pudding.
Repeat layering until ingredients are gone, topping with pudding.
Chill. Add sugar and vanilla to cream and whip.
Spread on top of pudding.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and celery.
Drain off fat.
To beef mixture, add kidney beans, chopped jalapeno peppers and tomato soup.
Season with garlic powder, chili powder and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve topped with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: After shelling peas, wash and change the water three or four times until you are sure all the hulls and sand are removed.
Then place the peas in a saucepan and cover with water, along with the salt pork.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 2 1/2 hours or less until the peas are tender.
The water should just cover the peas.

title: watermelon cookies
directions: Beat together butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar. Stir in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Gradually add flour to mixture, beating well.
Add enough flour to mixture, beating well.
Add enough red food color to color dough.
Shape into a ball, cover and chill for 3 hours.

title: homemade yogurt
directions: In glass bowl, empty Jell-O; add boiling water, stir until dissolved.
Add buttermilk and chill.
Can add fruit or eat plain.

title: chutney-bacon brie
directions: Remove rind from top of cheese, cutting to within 1/2 inch of outside edges.
Place cheese on a microwave-safe dish and spread chutney over top.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Microwave, uncovered, at High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until the Brie softens to desired consistency, giving dish a half turn after 1 minute. Serve with unsalted crackers or fruit.
Yields 12 to 15 appetizer servings.

title: bacardi rum cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt cake pan.
Put chopped nuts on bottom of pan.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
Do not use mixer.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients thoroughly.
Add poppy seed and nuts.
Blend on medium speed of mixer.
Bake in Bundt pan (ungreased) at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pierogies
directions: Sift flour and salt in bowl add butter egg and warm water.
Mix all together, knead dough until smooth and like satin.
Divide and roll to 1/4 inch thick on floured board.
Put kraut in patties and seal edges.
Drop in boiling salt water for 5 minutes about 6 to 8 at a time.
Lightly brown pierogies in buttered skillet.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift
together	all dry ingredients.
Cream
shortening and sugar.
Blend
in
egg
and
applesauce.
Dissolve soda in boiling water. Add soda water alternately with dry ingredients blending well
after
each addition.
Mix in raisins and nuts. Bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: imitation "snickers" bars
directions: Melt morsels and shortening over hot water (not boiling). Stir until melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in an 8-inch foil-lined pan; spread evenly. Refrigerate about 15 minutes.
Return remaining chocolate mixture to low heat (over water).

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix cheese and cracker crumbs.
In a greased baking dish alternate layers of cheese mixture, asparagus, eggs and soup. Repeat and top with cheese-crumb mixture.
Pour melted butter over this.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until brown.
Serves 6.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Beat together sugar and shortening until light and fluffy. Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well. Stir in candies and nuts.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Press 3 to 4 more candies into each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen 3 1/2-inch cookies.

title: banana split heaven
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, combine crushed vanilla wafers and melted butter.
Mix and press into bottom of pan.
Top with vanilla pudding and slices bananas evenly over pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Drizzle hot fudge over top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Refrigerate.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Melt on low heat margarine and brown sugar.
Remove from heat and beat in this order:
sugar, eggs, flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes until done.
Cut into bars.

title: crab spread
directions: Heat soup. Add cream cheese; stir until well blended. Remove from heat and add crab meat, mayo, celery and onion. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: mediterranean vegetable casserole
directions: Prepare pasta according to package, drain.
While pasta is cooking, grease a 2 quart oven proof baking dish.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add onion, garlic, zucchini and bell peppers. Saute over medium heat until tender.
Add black pepper, oregano and stewed tomatoes.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for five minutes. Uncover and cook an additional 2 to 3 minutes to reduce liquid. Transfer half of the tomato sauce to prepared dish.
Top with half of the cooked pasta and half of the ricotta cheese.
Repeat layers and top with parmesan cheese.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until heated through.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: rib eye roast
directions: Coat roast with pepper.
Combine the rest of the ingredients; mix well.
Place roast in mixture.
Turn once to coat roast. Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Bake in the sauce at 300° for 2 or 3 hours or until medium rare.
Remove from oven and slice. The hot marinade may be poured over sliced roast.

title: ives scalloped potatoes
directions: Fry some bacon in a heavy skillet.
Remove bacon and drain off excess fat.

title: wild game gumbo
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil and cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until tender. Remove from broth; chill broth.
Remove fat from broth.
Remove chicken from bones and chop into bite size pieces; set aside. Combine dove breasts and next 8 ingredients in a large Dutch oven. Add water to cover.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 2 hours.
Remove meat from broth.
Strain broth.
Set aside.
Brown sausage in a large heavy skillet over medium heat.
Remove to paper towel, leaving drippings in skillet.
Add bacon drippings to skillet; heat over medium heat until hot.
Add flour and cook, stirring constantly, 15 to 20 minutes until roux is caramel color.

title: layered chicken salad #814
directions: In a medium glass bowl, layer 1/2 each of the following ingredients in this order:
cooked chicken, water chestnuts, alfalfa sprouts and onion rings.
Sprinkle with half of the dressing and half of the pepper.
Repeat layers and sprinkle with remaining dressing and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve cold.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter or margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and almond extracts.

title: cheese puff canapes
directions: Preheat broiler.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Fold in cheese, Worcestershire sauce, paprika and mustard.
Toast bread rounds or crackers under broiler.
Spread untoasted side with mixture.
Place under broiler for approximately 6 minutes until the cheese is well puffed and brown.

title: quiche
directions: Put meat in pie pan first.
Then mix together rest of ingredients and pour over meat.
Top with mushrooms or green pepper.
Bake pie crust at 450° for 5 minutes before filling. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place 1/2 cup buttermilk in a medium bowl.
Mix seasoning salt, seasoned pepper and flour in another bowl.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Then put margarine in pan and melt in the oven. Dip chicken in the 1/2 cup buttermilk then in flour.
Place skin side down in pan.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Turn and bake another 15 minutes.
Mix rest of buttermilk, parsley and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Bake another 15 minutes (may need to bake longer if your oven is slow).
Sprinkle parsley and a bit of paprika across top before serving.

title: tropical pork chops
directions: Brown the chops in a little shortening.
Remove and sprinkle rice in the pan.
Pour orange juice over the rice and arrange chops over this.
Pour soup over all.
Cover and simmer until the rice has absorbed all the liquid and chops are tender.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Measure sugar, celery seed, salt and mustard into a jar with a tight fitting cover.
Add onion, vinegar and oil.
Shake vigorously.
Serve on fruit, salad greens or Sweet Tart Salad.

title: satin pie for 6
directions: Mix chocolate, milk, sugar and salt over hot water in top of double boiler until blended and smooth.
Cool slightly.
Add egg yolks, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add to chocolate mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix the apples, Cool Whip and 1/2 of the peanuts.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Sprinkle Jell-O over this mixture.
Add drained pineapple.
Let chill several hours.

title: luau cole slaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper; chill. Just before serving, add cabbage and orange sections.
Toss until evenly coated.
Add cubed cranberry sauce; toss lightly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry-rhubarb puff
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In ungreased baking pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches, mix rhubarb, strawberries and 1/2 cup sugar; place in oven. Measure flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, the baking powder and salt into bowl.
Pour oil and milk into measuring cup (do not stir together); pour all at once into flour mixture.
Stir until mixture cleans side of bowl and forms a ball.
Drop dough by 9 spoonfuls onto hot fruit.
Make an indentation in each biscuit; dot with butter.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon; sprinkle on biscuits.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yields 9 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: In mixer bowl, slightly beat eggs and add first five ingredients.
Blend well.
Add pecans and pour into shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then lower temperature to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in buttered baking dish; top with chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and milk; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over chicken mix.
Top with bread cubes.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: super pancakes
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, oil, flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
If it is too thick, add a little more milk.
Enjoy.

title: ham-vegetable chowder
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, cook broccoli with cheese sauce in pouch according to directions.
In same saucepan, combine the cooked broccoli with cheese sauce, corn and ham.
Stir in cream.
Cook until heated through, stirring occasionally.
Serve immediately. Serves 4.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet peppers

title: cheesy french bread
directions: Slice bread not quite all the way through.
Insert 1/4-inch slice cheese in each section.
Melt butter; stir in onion and poppy seed.
Pour over top of bread and sprinkle with paprika. Wrap in foil, leaving an opening on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: harvest pumpkin pie
directions: In
large
bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon, salt, cloves, pumpkin,
evaporated
milk	and eggs.
Blend well.	Fold 1 1/2 cups
whipped
topping
and pecans into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into crust	and
bake
at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and
continue	baking	40 to 45 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Cool.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain.
If using fresh or frozen green beans; cook until tender and drain.

title: debbie's deviled eggs
directions: Hard-boil eggs.
Peel eggs.
Slice eggs in half longways. Separate whites and yolks.
Mix yolks with all ingredients (except the paprika).
Blend with mixer on medium speed until creamy. Spoon mixture back into each egg white.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: marinated asparagus
directions: Sprinkle herbs on asparagus.
Pour dressing and vinegar on top. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chili
directions: Mix all together
and
cook over medium heat 1 1/2 to 2 hours. This freezes well.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Blend in vinegar.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened or bubbly.
Add beets and butter or margarine.
Heat 10 minutes over low heat.

title: strawberry peach dessert
directions: Layer cake into bottom of 13x9inch baking dish. Top with drained peaches. Set aside. Whip cream with sugar; fold whipped cream and vanilla into rice. Layer on top of peaches. Top with strawberries slices.

title: aunt betty's mandarin orange salad
directions: Combine all liquid from mandarin oranges, orange juice and sherry and add enough water to make a quart.
Put in a pan and bring to a boil.
Dissolve jello in liquid and cool.

title: butter pecan dessert
directions: Crush crackers and mix with melted butter.
Press into pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Beat vanilla pudding and cold milk with electric mixer until stiff.
Add butter pecan ice cream. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.
Serve topped with Cool Whip and crushed Heath bars or top entire pan with Cool Whip and sprinkle crushed Heath bars on top.

title: little beef rolls
directions: Trim round steak of all fat. Cut into strips, about 1 1/2 x 3-inches. Salt and pepper meat. Place a sliver of garlic and a very small piece of bacon on meat. Roll up and secure with a toothpick. Roll in flour and brown in melted shortening. After all rolls are browned, drain off all fat from pan. Push meat aside and pour in mushroom soup. Add 1 can of water. Cover and cook over low heat until tender, about 1 hour, scraping bottom of skillet to keep from sticking. Add water when necessary. Very good served with mashed potatoes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cube steak, roll in flour and brown in cooking oil along with chopped onion.
Add garlic salt.
When lightly browned, drain excess oil.

title: oatmeal loaf
directions: Measure oatmeal into bowl along with the melted butter, eggs and milk.
Add flavorings.
Stir well.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add sugar and all ingredients.
Stir well.
Oil a loaf pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° to complete 1 hour in all or until bread tests done and light brown.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: green beans with lemon
directions: Bring 2 quarts water to a boil in a Dutch oven; add salt and beans.
Cook 7 to 8 minutes; drain.
Plunge into ice water to stop the cooking process; drain.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Precook carrots slightly but not too soft.
Put carrots in buttered casserole.
Cover with mixture of all ingredients.
Top this with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° until desired doneness.

title: krista's banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2 or 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine all ingredients and stir to blend.
Spoon batter into pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool completely before slicing.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: miss ellie's banana cake
directions: Grease 3 (8-inch) round pans; line with wax paper in bottoms. Mix cake as on package directions.
Mash 3 bananas; add to batter. Bake as directed; cool on racks.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar, cornstarch, and salt to make a paste with 1/8 cup of the water.
Set aside.
Boil 7/8 cup of the water and gradually add the paste, stirring constantly to prevent lumping.
Cook until thickened.
Cool for 2 hours.
Arrange sliced strawberries in pie shell.
Stir food coloring into cooled, glaze and pour over strawberries.
Cool completely; chill.
Top with cool whip.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with assorted chips or vegetables.
Refrigerate unused dip.

title: icebox raised rolls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and cool to lukewarm.
Soften cake yeast in lukewarm water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and stir in first mixture.
Add egg and stir in 2 cups flour; beat thoroughly. Then stir in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Make into rolls next morning and let rise about 3 hours before baking.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 30 rolls.

title: red snapper with lime juice
directions: Dust fillets lightly with mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Then put oil in a frying pan and saute fillets for about 5 minutes or until they are golden brown.
Turn and saute on other side. Serve with lime wedges.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in sugar, vegetable oil and vanilla until mixture thickens and is lemon colored.
Stir in zucchini.
Sift in flour with cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Fold in nuts.
Pour mixture into a 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Let loaves cool in the pans for 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: end-of-the-line ham casserole
directions: Combine soup and milk.
Layer with other ingredients in 8-cup casserole dish in the following order:
potatoes, meat, onion and sauce.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove lid; sprinkle top with cheese and bake, uncovered, for another 20 minutes.

title: lemon cheese coffeecake
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups cake mix, eggs, flour, yeast and warm water. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: one crust rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb into 1/2-inch pieces using small stalks.
Mix egg, sugar, flour, water and butter and let stand while getting the rhubarb and crust ready.
Pour the mix over the rhubarb in the shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry crumb cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk and vanilla; mix these in blender. Add Cool Whip with this in a large bowl.
Crumble half of cake in the bottom of 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Add half of creamed mixture, then top this with blueberries.
Repeat with another layer.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Delicious!!

title: cordon bleu
directions: Flatten chicken breasts.
Top each with cheese and then ham. Secure with toothpick.
In skillet, brown chicken, skin side down, in butter.
Stir in soup and milk.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Top with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Mix all but chips.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with chips.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: fried rice and cheese balls
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm. Take a handful of the rice mixture and place a cheese chunk in the middle.
Roll into a ball and roll again in the bread crumbs. Fry the rice ball as you would a meat ball.
Can add tomato sauce to the top, if desired.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Beat all ingredients except cake mix and pecans.
Put in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over mixture. Pour melted margarine over cake mix and sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: poppy seed bread with almond glaze
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: baked fish with potatoes and onions
directions: Arrange 1/2 of the potatoes in buttered 3-quart casserole. Top with 1/2 of the onion and 1/2 of the bell pepper.
Season with salt and black pepper.
Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon of the oregano. Arrange fish in 1 layer over vegetables.
Arrange remaining potatoes, onion and bell pepper over fish.
Season with salt, black pepper and remaining 1/4 teaspoon oregano; set aside.
Melt butter in medium saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in flour; cook until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour white sauce over casserole.
Cover and bake in preheated 375° oven 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, about 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: party punch
directions: In Large Punch Bowl, pour in juice and soda, mix well. Add ice cream. Top with pineapple and cherries. Enjoy!

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and marshmallows in large mixing bowl. Bring to boil the margarine, shortening, cocoa and Coke.	Pour over dry mixture
and
stir until marshmallows are completely melted.
Add buttermilk,
soda
and
eggs.
Mix, do not beat. Bake at 350° for 30	minutes
in
layers, 35 to 40 minutes in sheet pan.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and spices; set aside.
Cream oleo and brown sugar; add eggs.
Add pumpkin and milk; mix well.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 5-inch pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Wrap and store overnight before serving.

title: gingerbread boys
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar. Add molasses and egg; mix well. Combine the flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves, salt and nutmeg; gradually add to creamed mixture and mix well. Divide dough in half. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours. On a lightly floured surface, roll out each portion of dough to 1/8-inch thickness. Cut with a 4-inch cookie cutter dipped in flour. Place 2-inches apart on greased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes or until edges are firm. Remove to wire racks to cool. Decorate as desired. Yield: About 2 dozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan; add egg yolks and milk and cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove; add peanut butter and stir.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon bubble loaf
directions: You will need two 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer first 7 ingredients in order given. Sprinkle sugar on top of mayonnaise, then add Cheddar.
Add bacon bits for decoration.

title: cream cheese and jelly dip
directions: Blend all together.
Serve with cream cheese and Sociables crackers.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix equal parts of each ingredient.
Makes an elegant punch.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar and add remaining ingredients. Grease pizza pan; spread dough.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool.

title: cranberry clafouti
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Cook cranberries in water or juice for 5 minutes, covered, on low heat.
Drain cranberries and boil down until 1/4 cup.
In blender, combine eggs, sugar, flour, milk, vanilla and cream.
Stir in cranberry liquid.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring to rolling boil.
Add fresh dill and pour over cucumbers.

title: chocolate sheet cake(brownies)
directions: Sift sugar, flour and salt.
In a saucepan, bring Crisco, butter, water and cocoa to a boil.
Pour over flour mixture while still hot.
Add buttermilk, beaten eggs, soda and vanilla; don't overbeat.
Bake in well-greased cookie sheet pan with sides, two 8 x 8-inch cake pans or a 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
While cake is baking, make icing.

title: spanish dip
directions: Fry hamburger and sausage together; drain.
Mix in crock-pot with remaining ingredients and cook until cheese is melted.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; add pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Stir well and pour into 13 x 8 x 2-inch glass casserole dish.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: oven fried fish, chicken or veal
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam. Put crumbs in bag. Spread mayonnaise on each piece of meat. Shake with crumbs. Bake 8 minutes at 450°. Do not over cook fish, chicken or veal.

title: dunking platters
directions: Blend margarine and sugars.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in oatmeal and cornflakes.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Stir in nuts and raisins as desired. Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients then pineapple, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix until blended.
Put in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage stuffed zucchini
directions: Trim off ends of zucchini and scoop out center of each, leaving a wall and base of about 1/2 inch or less.
Reserve scooped out pulp.
Chop enough pulp to make 3/4 cup.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend ingredients in blender and serve with assorted fruits as a dip.

title: overnight buns
directions: Bring water, 1 cup sugar, lard and salt to a boil.
Dissolve 1 teaspoon of sugar and yeast in warm water.
Add to first mixture when cool.
Add a little flour and beaten eggs.
Then add about 5 cups of flour.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all together and fry in shallow oil.
Drop by spoonfuls. (I mix everything except squash, saving it until ready to fry, because of water in squash.)

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients together, then add the next 6 ingredients.
Beat all together.
Add cherries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.
This should be cold before you remove it from the pan.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Slice washed cucumbers and let stand in lime water 24 hours. Drain and wash thoroughly.
Cover with clear water for 3 hours. Drain and wash again.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into bite size pieces.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Slice onion; place on top of tomatoes.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Add salad dressing; do not stir.
Sprinkle parsley on top.
Marinate 6 hours or more.
Just before serving, stir all ingredients.
Good next day, also.

title: bob forman italian meatball stew(crock-pot)
directions: Combine beef with bread crumbs, eggs, milk, cheese, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Form into 2-inch balls.

title: fudge drop cookies
directions: Melt morsels, butter and milk in a double boiler.
Remove from heat and gradually add flour until mixed.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 300°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread out into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add topping.

title: fruit salad
directions: Thaw strawberries and mix with pineapple and juice in which bananas have been sliced.
Let stand together for 4 hours in refrigerator to chill and blend flavors.

title: five hour stew
directions: Put everything in Dutch oven.
Cook at 250° for 5 hours. Makes a thick broth all its own!
Serves 4.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix and drop on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 300°.

title: ritz cracker chicken
directions: Salt chicken pieces and dip in melted margarine.
Roll each piece in crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and eggs; add flour and milk alternately. Add vanilla.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) layer pans and bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: dirt cups
directions: Crush cookie in food processor or plastic bag with rolling pin.
Pour milk in a large bowl; add pudding mix.
Beat until well mixed, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and half of the crushed cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon of crushed cookies on the bottom of 8 to 10 (7 ounce) cups.
Fill cups about 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining crushed cookies.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Decorate with gummy worms, candy flowers or chopped peanuts.

title: "red lobster" hot rolls
directions: Mix vigorously Bisquick, milk and Cheddar cheese.
Drop by spoonful on greased baking pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 450°. Brush on melted butter.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Serve warm.

title: punch
directions: Make 1 batch 2 to 3 days before needed and freeze.
Then on day needed, mix up another batch and add frozen batch so it will be slushy.

title: at ease macaroni and cheese
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt and a dash of pepper.
Gradually stir in milk and cheese.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and smooth.
Stir in sour cream and macaroni.
Heat through (do not boil).
Serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until partly done; drain.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Combine sour cream and soup.
Add to squash. Put half of the squash mixture into a greased casserole dish. Sprinkle 1 cup stuffing over mixture.
Add rest of squash mixture. Cover with rest of stuffing.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix stuffing mix and melted oleo.
Press 1/2 of the mixture in a baking or casserole dish.
Spread the squash over the stuffing. Mix sour cream, onions and cream of chicken soup.
Spread over squash.
Add rest of stuffing mix and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frosted nuts
directions: Mix sugar and sour cream.
Bring to boil and continue boiling for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Add nuts and stir until mixture begins to sugar.
Pour on waxed paper; separate and cool thoroughly.
Pack in air tight container.
Will keep 3 months.
Best stored in refrigerator.

title: low-fat banana pudding
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients and cook over medium heat until thickened.
In a deep-dish glass bowl, layer with vanilla wafers, banana slices and mixture.
May be topped with meringue topping or Cool Whip.

title: mom's brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in large kettle.
Cook over low to medium heat for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: harold's health cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine eggs, brown sugar, corn syrup, molasses and honey.
Beat until well blended with electric mixer.
Add remaining ingredients to egg mixture and beat until well mixed.

title: apple slices (danish apple bars)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Cut in lard.
Add egg yolk mixed with milk.
Mix dough just enough to hold together.
Cut dough in half and roll one portion into 11 x 15-inch rectangle. Transfer to cookie sheet.
Spread crushed corn flakes on this pastry.
Spread sliced apples over corn flakes.
Cover apples with sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Cover with remaining half pastry rolled out.
Pinch edges together.
Beat egg white until stiff and spread on top of pastry.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and while still hot, drizzle glaze over top.

title: cherokee pie casserole
directions: Saute onion in olive oil.
Brown meat in sauteed onion.
Add spices, soup, tomatoes and rice.
Cook together 3 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole pan.
Cut cheese diagonally and place on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and bubbles, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Good served with green salad.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until done.

title: potato chowder
directions: Cook vegetables in water until tender; add ham (I sometimes use part summer sausage), cheese and milk.
Simmer gently until cheese melts.
May be thickened, if desired.
Garnish with parsley on side and croutons afloat.

title: miracle rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking soda.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Mix well; turn out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly a few times.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for about 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine creamed corn, chili with beans, tamales and shredded cheese. Bake 15 minutes in preheated oven at 375°.
Stir.
Sprinkle top with 3/4 cup crushed tortilla chips and 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake 10 more minutes. Garnish with shredded lettuce and ripe olives.

title: cheddar and cauliflower soup
directions: Saute leeks in butter until wilted (3 minutes); add carrots and cauliflower.
Stir to coat with butter.
Add broth and seasonings.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes, until vegetables are soft. Puree in small batches, then return to heat.
Add Cheddar cheese; let melt.
Serve with garnish of chives and parsley.
This soup is great and healthy too!

title: pecan balls
directions: Mix together and form into small balls.
Bake about 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and saute eggplant in 2 tablespoons butter until tender. Drain and mash.
Mix in order given.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with 1 cup toasted bread crumbs with 1 stick oleo.
Bake at 250° until brown.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in oleo.
Add soups, chicken broth, pimento, mushrooms and chicken.
Cook slowly until well heated.
Cook spaghetti until tender.
Drain.
Put layer of spaghetti, layer of sauce, grated cheese and Parmesan cheese. Repeat layers to top of dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Serves 8 to 10.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix strong hot tea, sugar, cinnamon and cloves well.
Add orange juice, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Mix all well.
Let set to blend flavors.
Serve hot, keeping stirred up as the spices will settle out.
Will keep for a couple of weeks in refrigerator.

title: chicken and black-eyed pea stew
directions: Cook chicken over medium heat in oil, until brown on all sides, in a large heavy pan or Dutch oven.
Spoon off fat.
Add chicken broth, vegetables, garlic, pepper sauce, salt, thyme and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until thickest pieces of chicken are done, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel jello
directions: Remove loose salt from pretzels.
Mix together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.

title: creamy turkey and broccoli
directions: In medium saucepan, cook broccoli according to package directions; drain and set aside.
In same pan, blend Cup-a-Soup with milk; cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes or until boiling.
Spoon half of soup into quart casserole dish.
Top with turkey and broccoli, then remaining soup.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry diced bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Simmer onion in bacon fat.
Add the flour, water, sugar and vinegar.
Cook until thick.
Pour over sliced potatoes.
Sprinkle with bacon. Serve warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain, then blend with mushroom soup, egg, mayonnaise and onion.
Top with shredded cheese and crackers. Bake uncovered at 350° until bubbly in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: california broccoli salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and pour over cauliflower and broccoli.
Marinate overnight.

title: super cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, milk and
pudding.
Spread over cooled cake.
Spread pineapple over pudding mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove, drain, cool, then crumble.
Pour out all grease drippings, reserve 2 teaspoons in the skillet.
Add onions and pepper; cook until tender.
Add the other ingredients and cook for 15 minutes on low heat.
You can use your own canned tomatoes, if you have them.

title: strawberry citrus punch
directions: In a blender container, puree the preserves and lemon juice. In a large punch bowl, combine strawberry mixture, water and orange juice (thawed) concentrate.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and ice ring, if desired. Very good and pretty at Christmas.

title: okra and sausage creole
directions: In a large, heavy-duty pot, heat olive oil.
Saut onion, parsley, green onion and bell pepper until onions are clear.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, soy sauce, garlic, water and sausage. Cover and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until it comes to a boil.
Add okra, salt, and hot sauce and simmer on low until okra is tender, about 45 minutes.
The longer it cooks, the better the taste.

title: date nut roll
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, dates, nuts and eggs.
Cook 10 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add Rice Krispies.
Let cool until you can handle.
Form a log and roll in flake coconut.
Keep in refrigerator and slice as needed.

title: chili soup
directions: Fry onion and hamburger (brown).
Heat tomato juice, sugar, chili powder, salt and water to boiling point.
Reserve some water to dissolve cornstarch.
Add hamburger and cornstarch thickening and keep stirring until thickened.
Add beans.
Cook for 5 minutes.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, drain and set aside. In a skillet or saucepan, saute onions in butter until tender. Stir in soup and salt. Heat until bubbly. In a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish arrange half of broccoli. Top with half of boiled eggs, half of cheese and half of mushroom soup. Repeat layers, Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes. Sprinkle onion rings on top and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: cajun mushrooms
directions: Put butter, pepper and Worcestershire sauce in a large skillet and cook on high heat.
Add mushrooms when butter is melted; cook on high, stirring regularly.
Cook until mushrooms look glazed and sauce is reduced.
Add onions and continue cooking until onions are soft.
Serve with crackers with cold wine or beer.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix Jell-O with whipped topping and juice from cherries.
Add 2 cups cherries and chopped pecans.
Dissolve Jell-O well and put in crushed wafers and let set until jelled.

title: scalloped spinach
directions: Cook spinach; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except crumbs.
Mix and pour into 1-quart greased casserole.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in cold water for several hours or overnight. Put dill, garlic and cucumbers in jars.
Pack tightly.
Bring the vinegar, salt and water to a boil, then pour over cucumbers.
Let cool to seal.

title: oatmeal-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Add next 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in the oats and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spanish pickled okra
directions: In large saucepan combine vinegar, water and salt and bring to boil.
In bottom of jar place dill seed, garlic, mustard seed and chili pepper.
Pack in jars filled with okra.
Pour boiling liquid over okra.
Seal jars.
Water bath for 10 minutes.

title: old time jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat egg yolks until light. Put in soda, sugars and butter. Add spices and cocoa. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into mixture. Add jam and raisins.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately beginning and ending with flour. Bake in large pan for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: creamy pea salad(makes 24 servings)
directions: Combine first seven ingredients, stirring gently.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Stir in bacon and cashews.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: pineapple cream dressing(fruit dip)
directions: Melt butter on heat controlled top burner set at 150° or in a double boiler.
Blend in flour.
Add sugar and egg yolk.
Mix well, then stir in pineapple juice and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Fold beaten egg whites into hot mixture.
After it cools, store in refrigerator and thin with whipping cream as used.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Melt peanut butter and butter together in a bowl over boiling water.
Mix other ingredients.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix egg, brown sugar, oil, vanilla and some buttermilk. Alternate dry ingredients and rest of buttermilk.
Mix in nuts and rhubarb last.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Last 1/2 hour bake at 325°.

title: dora's corn casserole
directions: Mix and spoon into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with grated cheese and dot with sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in frying pan.
Drain off fat. Combine all ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Spread onto pizza pan or any pan.
Top and bake.

title: cornmeal banana-nut bread
directions: Stir together 1 cup cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix beaten eggs, mashed ripe bananas and cooking oil.
Add to dry ingredients; stir just enough to moisten.
Add chopped walnuts.

title: simple fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Chill.
Pour over ice in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.
Delicious, refreshing but not too sweet.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter and cream to soft ball stage.
Cool and put in vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour in buttered pan.

title: taco beans
directions: Boil pintos until about 1/2 done.
Add link sausage, seasonings and package of taco seasoning.
Cook until done.

title: oatmeal honey cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheet with butter flavor Crisco.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, egg, honey, granulated sugar, water and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat on low speed of electric mixer until blended.
Increase speed to medium.
Beat until light and creamy.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add gradually to creamed mixture at low speed.
Increase speed to medium.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in oats with spoon.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 3 to 5 minutes on baking sheet before moving to flat surface.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.
For small cookies, drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 dozen small cookies.

title: apple-oat muffins
directions: In large bowl, mix first 5 ingredients.
In small bowl, beat honey, milk, oil and egg until blended; stir in flour until moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.)
Fold in apples.
Spoon batter into muffin tins, coming almost to top of each cup.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of muffin comes out clean.
Bake at 350°.
Remove from pan.
Serve warm or cool.

title: heavenly rice pudding
directions: Mix cold cooked rice, marshmallows, pineapple, cherries and nuts in a bowl.
Chill evaporated milk in refrigerator tray until soft ice crystals form around edges of tray (15 to 20 minutes). Whip until stiff (1 minute).
Add lemon juice; whip very stiff (2 minutes).
Beat in powdered sugar.
Fold whipped Carnation into rice mixture.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons of flour, salt and pepper in a clean paper bag.
Add chicken pieces and shake to coat.
Beat eggs with milk.
Mix remaining flour and sesame seed.
Dip each breast piece into egg mixture, then roll in sesame mixture to coat.
Lower into hot, deep oil and fry at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden and tender.
Drain and serve with Supreme Sauce.
Serves 4.

title: cinnamon munch
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon. Set aside. In a large skillet, melt butter over low heat.
Add Chex.
Heat and stir gently until all pieces are coated.
Continue to heat and stir 5 to 6 minutes.

title: nanny's divinity fudge
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Make syrup of sugar, water and Karo syrup.
Boil until syrup "threads" from spoon.
Add vanilla. Place on buttered plate and allow to stand until hard enough to eat.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Sift flour and soda 3 times; mix sugar, butter and sour cream.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt and flavoring to well-creamed mixture.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each one added.
Add flour.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Melt cheese in milk in a double boiler with low heat.
Add all other ingredients.
Makes 1 quart.
Keeps for weeks in fridge!

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine mix, milk and cheese.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown. Combine melted butter and garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, vanilla and Rice Krispies in large bowl.
Add butter.
Form into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and wax in a double boiler.
Keep on heat and dip balls into chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper to cool.
Freezes well.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread 1/2 of cream cheese on dinner plate.
Cover with half of chili and then spread half of Cheddar cheese over top.
(You can make 2 plates to use up ingredients.
Store covered in refrigerator until ready to use.)
Put in microwave for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Mix soda with flour and milk.
Add to butter.
Add bananas and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: emily's pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in a heavy saucepan. Cook until syrup spins a thread or reaches the soft ball stage. Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Yields about 18 pralines.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add vinegar.
Add this mixture to mayonnaise, stirring to prevent lumping.
Drain as much liquid from cucumbers as possible.
Combine cucumber, cottage cheese and onion.
Add to mayonnaise mixture.
Add pecans and pour into mold. Chill several hours.

title: four minute brownie pie
directions: Place everything, except nuts, in bowl; beat 4 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased pie tin and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: spicy meat pie
directions: Saute meat, onion and garlic in large skillet.
Stir in next 6 ingredients.
Mix cornstarch and water; stir in gradually.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Prepare pastry.

title: ham-cheese appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients; spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown (25 to 30 minutes).
Cut into rectangles (about 2 x 2 1/2-inch).
Makes 36 appetizers.

title: salsa stuffed peppers
directions: Slice and saute one green pepper.
Add next three ingredients.
Mix well.
Heat.
Stuff remaining 6 peppers.
Place in glass pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: amaretto creme on fresh fruit
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, for 6 to 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in Amaretto and vanilla.
Cover and chill.
Serve cold.

title: panfish cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill for several hours and form into a ball.
Roll in Cheddar cheese and nuts.
This is a soft spread and forms better if it is left in the refrigerator overnight before rolling in cheese.

title: baked apples
directions: Mix jello, sugar and water and bring to a boil.
Add apples and boil 10 minutes; remove apples to baking dish and pour syrup over apples.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Keeps week or more refrigerated.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble.
Remove from pan and drain off some of bacon drippings.
Saute onion in same pan.
Add beaten eggs and add in crumbled bacon.
Cook like scrambled eggs.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream margarine, cheese and sugar.
Add flour.
Refrigerate overnight.
Form into small balls and roll in sugar.
Flatten; put pecan half on top and bake at 350° on a greased baking sheet for 15 minutes.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples, core and cut in lengths.
Arrange in shell.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar and flour.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Cool before cutting.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine
cornbread,
flour,
baking powder, salt, sugar and milk;
make
a
well
in center of mixture.
Combine eggs, water and
oil;
add
to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened. Fold in corn and remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into a greased
x
x
2-inch
pan.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes or until
a knife inserted in center comes out clean. Yields 15 servings.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix together ingredients. Crumble this with your hands and put half the mixture in an 8-inch square pan. Pour 1 can cherry pie filling over that, then sprinkle the remaining mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine and drop by teaspoon into deep fryer.
Cook until golden brown.

title: cheese broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli to thaw; drain.
Saute onion in oleo.
Add remaining ingredients and heat until cheese melts.
Add broccoli and stir.
Serve hot with chips.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: cocktail punch
directions: Combine sugar and water; boil 10 minutes until sugar dissolves, stirring.
Cool.
Mix grapefruit juice and orange juice and chill.
Just before serving, add cold ginger ale and grenadine.

title: chocolate oatmeal bars
directions: Melt butter. Stir in brown sugar and Karo. Slowly blend in oats. Line baking pan with foil and rub with margarine. Spread mixture over pan to desired thickness. Bake at 350° about 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are brown. Cool.

title: chinese tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff for 50
directions: Cut beef in 1/4-inch wide strips.
Coat well with flour and salt.
Brown in skillet in fat.
Add mushroom slices, onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is slightly tender, 3 to 5 minutes. Remove meat, mushrooms and onion from pan.
Melt butter in pan drippings.
Add flour; cook until froth-like.
Add tomato paste and bouillon; cook until thick, stirring continuously.
Add meat and heat.
Stir in sour cream; heat, but do not boil.
Serve on rice or noodles.
Serving size:
one cup each.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix together margarine, flour and nuts and spread in a 9x12 pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees - cool.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add flour, sugar, milk, vanilla, baking powder, salt and butter.
Mix until well blended.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes on greased cookie sheet. After removing from oven, spread with peanut butter while cake is hot.
Cool in refrigerator, then spread with melted chocolate bar.

title: yummie rolls
directions: Melt shortening in boiling water.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Makes a soft dough.
Let rise to double in size.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Stack two together with pat of butter between the two and a pat of butter on top.
Let rise.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: one-dish macaroni beef(microwave)
directions: Crumble ground beef into 2-quart glass casserole dish.
Stir in chopped onions; cover with glass lid.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Drain and stir in all remaining ingredients.
Recover with lid.
Microwave on Defrost or low temperature for 30 to 40 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Let stand 5 minutes, covered, before serving.

title: trader vic's crab rangoon
directions: Clean cauliflower and let dry.
Heat oil. Drop into hot oil just a few minutes. Drain.
Add salt or seasonings to taste. Fast, easy and good.

title: hamburg stew
directions: Brown hamburg with onion and green pepper.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer.

title: three corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients with electric mixer and mix until moistened. Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: camper's chowder(quick and easy)
directions: With 1 can of water, rinse out all of the cans and add to the soup.
Heat and enjoy.

title: cranberry punch
directions: *Or use 1 envelope (2 quart size) Kool-Aid sugar sweetened soft drink mix.

title: banana puff cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon in a bowl. Cut in shortening.
Add egg, banana, rolled oats and chocolate chips.
Beat until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Do not overbake.

title: waldorf broccoli salad
directions: Prepare broccoli and fruit as directed in a mixing bowl. Every item is raw. Mix slaw dressing, vinegar, mayonnaise and sugar; blend until smooth. Pour over broccoli mixture; chill.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: In a double boiler, melt candy bars with half the cream.
Beat eggs in remaining cream.
Whisk into melted chocolate.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Beat milk and pudding mixes.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Pour into mixing bowl. Mix well and pour into 3 round pans or 2 square ones. Bake 20 to 30 minutes. Let cool before frosting.

title: betty's oyster nips
directions: Pour all ingredients over oyster crackers.
Toss, let set one hour.
Toss again before serving.
Keep in closed container.

title: open-faced pizza sandwiches
directions: Cook ground beef until browned, stirring to crumble; drain. Return meat to skillet.
Add spaghetti sauce mix and tomato paste. Stir well.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture is bubbly.
Spoon meat mixture on muffin halves.
Top each with 3 pepperoni slices.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake an additional 3 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered. Uncover last 45 minutes and stir every 10 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Put milk and marshmallows in double boiler.
Heat, stirring until melted and mixed well.
Chop fruit and nuts; place in crumb mixture.
Add marshmallows and milk mixture to fruit and crumb mixture.
Stir until mixed well.
Pour mixture into a wax paper lined tube pan.
Press mixture firmly in pan.
Place in refrigerator.
Let stand about 2 days; remove from pan.
Keep uneaten cake in refrigerator.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Thoroughly chill can of milk in refrigerator overnight. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add honey, salt, lemon juice and rind.
Refrigerate.
When it has congealed slightly, beat milk until stiff and whip gelatin mixture into it.
Spread half of crumbs into a large pan (10 x 13-inch or equivalent) and pour lemon mixture over it.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Chill for approximately 3 hours.
May be served plain or with whipped cream.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Mix other ingredients together.

title: chocolate ho ho's
directions: Make as directed.
Bake only 15 to 18 minutes.
Put on jelly roll pan or cookie sheet with about 1-inch sides.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Oil a 2-quart casserole.
Set aside.
Cook macaroni, without salt, following package directions.
Drain well. Heat oil in large skillet on medium heat.
Add onions and garlic. Saute until tender.
Stir in flour, basil, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Blend well.
Blend in milk slowly.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add cheese pieces.
Stir until smooth.

title: quick beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add extra bacon to top, if desired.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut candy, dates and nuts in small pieces.
Mix into flour. Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Put soda in milk.
Mix into dry mixture, pour into large tube pan (floured and greased).
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: quick beef soup
directions: Brown meat with onion until onion is tender; drain (to remove grease).
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: merry bars
directions: Cook that on the left side for 5 min. Put in the 8 c. Rice Krispies.
Stir it in. Put it in a pan.
Press it down.
Later on, cut it in pieces.

title: christmas fruit sticks
directions: Chop first 4 ingredients.
Mix with coconut and milk.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with brown paper.
Pour mixture into pan and pat firmly.
Bake at 275° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand for 10 minutes.
Turn out onto waxed paper sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Cool 1 hour and cut in strips or squares.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; beat at medium speed 2 minutes (batter will be thin).

title: molten chocolate cakes
directions: Coat 16 muffin cups with melted butter. Sprinkle with cocoa. Refrigerate until firm.

Place butter pieces and chocolate in a big heavy pan or iron skillet. Cook over low heat, stirring often, until butter and chocolate melt. Slowly whisk in cream; set aside. Mix egg substitute and sugar in a big mixing bowl. Beat at medium speed with electric mixer about 7 minutes or until blended. Pour batter into muffin cups, filling to 1/4-inch from top. Cover and chill 1 to 24 hours. Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 10 to 11 minutes or just until edges of cakes

spring back when lightly touched, but centers are still soft. Let stand 3 minutes before loosening edges with a knife. Quickly invert cakes onto a baking sheet. Transfer to plates using a spatula. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serve immediately. Yield: 16.

title: sausage cheese biscuits
directions: Cook sausage until well done; drain.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup milk and nuts.
Spread 1/2 of mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 6 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and store in an airtight container.
Makes 32 cups mix.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter; add remaining ingredients.
Spread in 13 x 8 x 2-inch buttered pan.
Cut into pieces.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Spray 2-quart casserole with nonstick cooking spray.
Place margarine in 4-cup Pyrex measure.
Microwave uncovered on High 15 to 30 seconds or until melted.
Stir in flour, mustard, salt and pepper until margarine is absorbed.
Gradually stir in milk. Microwave uncovered 4 to 5 minutes, stirring after every minute, until thickened.
Layer 1/3 of the potatoes, 1/2 of the ham, 1/2 of the onion and 1/3 of the sauce; repeat the layers.
Top with remaining potatoes and sauce.
Cover tightly and microwave on Medium High (70%) 16 to 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, combine all beans, onion, bacon and vinegar, mixing well.
In a bowl, combine brown sugar, mustard, garlic and salt.
Add to beans and stir in well.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: homemade dog biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Roll out half of the dough at a time into 3/8-inch thickness.
Cut to desired shapes. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 375°.
Turn off the oven and leave the biscuits in oven until cool.
Yields about one pound.

title: lemon swirl frosting
directions: Blend together until smooth.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix meat together thoroughly.
Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add meat and mix.
Saute onion in large skillet in 2 tablespoons butter.
Mix together seasonings, eggs, onion and meat in bowl. Mix well; form into 48 small balls.
Melt butter in skillet; brown meatballs on all sides.
Remove; set aside to make sauce.

title: roasted ham
directions: Cook the ham at 350° for 40 minutes for every pound.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together sugar, salt and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until very light.
Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Blend into first mixture until well blended.
Do not beat too much after beating in eggs.
Shape into small balls (about the size of a walnut).
Roll in sugar and spice mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
These will puff up and flatten as they cool.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: ham hocks and greens
directions: In a large pot, brown ham hocks in oil or place ham bone in pot. Add water and onion, bringing to a boil.
Add greens and return liquid to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer
1 1/2 or 2 hours.
Drain.
Remove ham and cut meat into bite-sized pieces. Add meat to greens.

title: mrs. field's cookies ala barb
directions: *Chocolate chips and pecans can be replaced with white chocolate chunks and Macadamia nuts.

title: chicken broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken and rice.
Combine chicken, rice, broccoli and cheese.
Place in dish and bake until completely heated at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: italian cream squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until blended.
Add coconut and pecans.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Boil molasses to rolling boil.
Add vinegar and soda.
Stir in sugar.
Use large saucepan; may foam over top.
Remove from stove and stir in eggs, ginger, salt and flour.
Will be stiff enough to roll out on floured board.
Cut with round cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: dot's cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, combine oats, sugars, flour and salt.
Combine soda and water.
Stir into oats, mixing along with oil and vanilla.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from the oven.
Allow to stand 2 minutes before removing to cool.
Yields about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix soda with mashed bananas.
Add to first mixture.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter casserole.
Add apples.
Pour water over apples and sprinkle on cinnamon.
Blend together the sugar, flour and butter; spread over apples.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 375°. Serves 6, unless grandson, Jordan, is visiting - his favorite dessert!

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and 2 cups sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to creamed mixture.
Place flour in large bowl and add dates, orange slices and nuts.
Stir to coat each piece.

title: chicken and pork adobo
directions: In medium saucepan, combine vinegar, garlic, pepper, bay leaf and soy sauce.
Add chicken and pork.
Turn and let soak for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add water and simmer uncovered until tender.
Remove meat.
Strain sauce; add bread crumbs and set aside.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Mix well and let it set for a few hours.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: german pickled mushrooms(eingelegte champignons)
directions: Wash mushrooms thoroughly in cold water containing 1 tablespoon salt; drain.
Mix all other ingredients; pour over the mushrooms in an enameled saucepan.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 6 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Let cool.
Keep covered in a refrigerator until required.
This is one of my favorite first courses.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate almond truffles
directions: In a small, heavy saucepan, melt together the chocolate and butter, stirring occasionally until melted.
Remove from heat. Stir together the powdered sugar and 2/3 cup ground almonds.
Stir into the chocolate mixture along with the milk or liqueur.
Mix well until blended.
Cover and chill mixture until firm, about 1 to 2 hours.
Use a round teaspoonful of mixture for candy.
Mold the chocolate mixture around a whole almond to form a ball.
If desired, roll balls in chocolate, cocoa powder or ground almonds to coat.
Put candy in foil.
Put in freezer 30 minutes.

title: boiled-raisin-cake
directions: Simmer raisins in margarine or butter and 1 cup water until plump.
Set aside to cool.
In another bowl, put in all remaining ingredients and 1/2 cup water.
Beat, then add walnuts and raisin mixture.
In glass 7 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch pan, bake at 325° longer than 40 minutes.
In 7 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch tin, bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: tofu veg enchiladas
directions: Saute all ingredients (except tortillas) until tender, then wrap in corn tortillas.
Pour peanut butter sauce over enchiladas and top with cheese if desired.

title: hawaiian coconut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut.
Chill at least 1 hour. Roll in 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Chill.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: chili beef casserole
directions: In a heavy skillet, cook beef and onion, stirring occasionally until beef is brown slightly.
Drain.
Place in 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add beans, drained corn and chili powder.
Mix well.
Top with corn chips. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake in preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes until bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: low-fat chicken
directions: Mix honey and apple juice and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 1 hour.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until tender. Mix seasonings together; sprinkle over bread cubes. Add onion, celery and eggs. Add water or broth. Mix well. Bake at 350°.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix well.
There will be some lumps.
Grease muffin tin (6 muffin size).
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Press in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Beat sugar, eggs and butter for 15 minutes.
Spread over crumbs.
Cut bananas on top, then drained pineapple, then diced cherries.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: peanut bread
directions: Sift flour with soda and salt.
Blend sugar into peanut butter.
Stir in egg and beat until smooth.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately, beating until smooth after each addition. Pour into buttered loaf pan, 4 x 8 x 2 1/2-inches.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until well browned.
Makes one loaf.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot deep fat.
Fry until brown as you desire.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot.

title: bacon quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pie plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper in a medium size bowl with electric mixer until smooth, about 1 minute.
Pour into pie plate. Bake approximately 35 minutes or until top is golden brown and knife inserted between the center and edge comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Garnish with tomato slices and bacon strips.

title: tiger cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients. Add to batter. Stir in cereal. Mix well. Swirl in melted chocolate chips. Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Remove chicken from bone, pull into small pieces.
Mix chicken, onion, chili powder, garlic salt, soup and Ro-Tel.
Add mix and cheese, alternating in a well-greased 8 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch Pyrex dish until cheese tops dish.
Bake at 350° until well heated and cheese melts through.

title: cheese cake tarts
directions: Mix the crushed grahams and soft butter; set aside.
Mix and cream together the cream cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla.
Put 1 teaspoon of the graham mixture into small muffin cups.
Pour cream cheese mixture over graham mixture, 3/4 way up to top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 32 to 34 bite size tarts.
Pour small amount of cherry pie filling over.
Serve.

title: holiday turkey dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in a pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until brown.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: victoria crab cakes
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients, stir in crabmeat and 1 cup of bread crumbs.
Shape into 8 patties; dredge patties in remaining bread crumbs.
Fry in 2 tablespoons butter over medium heat until golden brown, adding additional butter as needed.
Drain on paper towels.
Garnish with lemon slices and parsley sprigs.

title: pork chop suey
directions: *Any type of meat may be used.

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayo and pineapple juice until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and freeze.
Thaw for 1 hour before serving.

title: sausage and gravy
directions: Melt margarine in a medium saucepan over medium heat.
Add sausage.
Cook uncooked sausage until it is brown, stirring to crumble.
Sprinkle with flour.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk, stirring until well blended. Cook over medium heat 8 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in pepper and salt.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Stir soda into molasses until foamy.
Add water, salt and ginger and set aside.
Mix flour and brown sugar and cut in shortening and margarine, then add cinnamon.
Stir until crumbly. Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry and pour in 1/3 of the molasses mixture.
Sprinkle 1/3 of the crumb mixture over and continue alternating layers with crumbs as top layer.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown on top.
(Although baked in a pie plate with a crust, this is not a pie but a very crumbly topping.)

title: butter toffee
directions: Combine sugar, salt and water.
Heat to boiling.
Add 1/2 of pecan meal and cook to 290°, stirring constantly.
Add remaining pecan meal.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Cool.
Brush with melted chocolate.

title: champagne punch
directions: Punch should be fairly slushy.

title: granny's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
Mix bread crumbs, egg and tomato juice; let soak until bread is completely wet.
Add this to the hamburger and onion.
Form in loaf pan. Mix last ingredients and spread over meat.
Bake 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned fudge
directions: Melt butter and cocoa, then add sugar, milk and salt.
Place over low heat and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to boil, without stirring, to soft ball stage.
Add vanilla and beat until cooled.
Pour into a greased pan.
Cool and cut into small squares.

title: fresh string bean soup
directions: Cook cut beans and potatoes in 5 cup salted water for 15 minutes.
In a frying pan, brown flour in oil.
Add paprika, black pepper and 1/4 cup cold water.
Stir until smooth.
Add sour cream.
Add this to the cooked beans and potatoes.
Bring to boil and simmer for a few more minutes.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, Miracle Whip and chili powder.
Layer meat, chips and cheese.
Repeat.
Bake for 20 minutes or until heated.
Top with shredded lettuce and tomatoes, if desired.

title: tomato salad with basil
directions: Slice and peel 5 to 7 tomatoes; add salt and basil to taste (lots of fresh basil torn up into small pieces).

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes very thin.
Combine milk, butter and flour.
Put 1/2 the potatoes in a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Pour half the sauce, half the onion and half the salt and pepper. Then put remainder of potatoes and sauce in dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for one hour.
Top with cheese and melt.

title: ambrosia
directions: Peel oranges; remove white membrane.
Cut oranges into 1/8-inch thick slices.
Peel bananas.
Cut on the diagonal into 1/8-inch slices.
Drain pineapple; reserve liquid.
In serving bowl, layer 1/2 of orange slices; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon confectioners sugar,
Layer 1/2 of banana slices and 1/2 of pineapple.
Sprinkle with half of coconut.
Repeat layering fruit and sugar.
Pour pineapple liquid over fruit.
Sprinkle remaining coconut.
Chill several hours.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: tomato creamed chipped beef(dried beef)
directions: Brown beef in water; add flour until brown.
Add milk to make a thick gravy.
Add tomatoes.
Cook slowly until well blended. Add eggs and cheese.
Serve on biscuits or English muffins.
Makes wonderful brunch served with scrambled eggs and fried apples. Serves 8.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; add water gradually and cook over boiling water until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Beat egg yolks and pour hot mixture over them gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
