Just before removing from heat, add lemon juice, rind and butter.
Mix well and cool.
Pour into pastry shell.
Top with meringue and proceed as directed.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and flavoring in a large bowl.
Add flour, bit by bit.
Work until dough is smooth.
Put dough into cookie press.
Press cookies onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 9 to 12 minutes.

title: green pepper steak
directions: With a very sharp knife, cut beef across grain into thin strips (1/8-inch thick).
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger together; add beef.
Toss and set aside.
While preparing vegetables, cook 30 to 40 minutes.
Heat oil in large frying pan or wok.
Add beef and toss over high heat until browned.
Add vegetables.
Toss until vegetables are tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and heat through.

title: old-fashioned meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into loaf and bake at 400° for 70 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: 2-step creamy chicken and pasta
directions: Cut up and brown chicken until done.
Add pasta blend, soup and water.
Cover and simmer until done.

title: mexican wedding rings
directions: Cream first three ingredients together after butter has come to room temperature.
Add flour and nuts.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Shape in small balls.
Place on cookie sheet, ungreased.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
When cold, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
What I generally do is place the powdered sugar in a small brown luncheon bag, place the cookies in the bag, 2 to 3 at a time, then gently shake the bag to coat the cookies.

title: easy corn pudding
directions: Spray casserole with nonstick baking spray.
Mix ingredients. Pour into casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: miso chicken
directions: Debone and flatten the thighs.
Mix the miso, sugar, shoyu and beer.
Marinate chicken in it overnight.
Broil the chicken over charcoal, basting occasionally.
Or bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, turning the chicken over halfway through the baking.

title: monkey bread
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or a Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Quarter ready-to-bake biscuits; roll quarters in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Melt margarine in pan and add brown sugar until dissolved.
Put biscuits in pan covering bottom of pan.
Pour brown sugar mixture over biscuits.
Top with nuts or raisins, if desired.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and Serve warm or cooled.

title: noodle entree
directions: Saute in oil until golden brown the Skallops, onion, mushrooms, yeast and salt.
Place the soup, cream cheese and milk in a double boiler; heat until well blended.
Mix all ingredients together and place in a large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill.

title: apple torte
directions: Mix butter and sugar until fluffy.
Mix in vanilla.
Add flour and mix well.
Spread on bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Mix soft cream cheese and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Pour into pan.
Mix apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Put over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Lower heat to 400°
and bake another 25 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: tomatoes and cauliflower
directions: Remove outer leaves and stalks from fresh cauliflower; separate into flowerets.
Cook in microwave until almost tender (approximately 8 minutes).
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, cook garlic and oil, uncovered, for about 2 minutes.
Remove garlic and add hot, drained cauliflower to oil.
Cook, uncovered, for about 4 minutes.
Add salt and tomatoes.
Cover and cook for about 6 minutes or until hot.
Stir once during cooking.
Just before serving, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel; crumble and set aside.
Drain fat from pan, reserving 2 tablespoons of drippings in skillet.
In drippings, cook onion and green pepper until tender.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, water, rice, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, chili powder, black pepper and hot sauce.
Cover.
Simmer about 30 minutes or until rice is done. Top with bacon. Sprinkle with shredded cheese, if desired.

title: baked ham medley
directions: Scrape gelatin and excess fat from ham, reserving 1/3 cup of the gelatin.
Make 4 evenly spaced slits in top of ham, about 1-inch deep.
Place ham and reserved gelatin in 10-inch round or 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Arrange apple slices and sweet potatoes around ham.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over all.
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for 1 1/4 hours, basting occasionally.
Remove from oven.
Cut cheese diagonally to form 4 triangles.
Insert one triangle in each ham slit.
Return the ham to the oven.
Bake 1 minute more, or just until cheese triangles melt slightly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Pour 2 cups batter into greased 13 x 9 pan; bake 15 minutes. In medium saucepan over low heat, melt caramels and margarine with Eagle Brand milk, stirring until smooth. Spread evenly over cake; spread remaining cake batter over caramel mixture. Top with pecans. Return to oven; bake 30 to 35 minutes longer, until cake springs back when lightly touched. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: raspberry muffins
directions: Combine raspberries, eggs, oil and sugar.
Beat well. Add the soda, salt, flour, cinnamon and baking powder.
Mix together well. Spray the muffin pans with any spray to prevent sticking.
Fill the muffin pans half full.
Bake at 350° until muffins spring back to the touch and are nice and golden.
(Check at 15 minutes.) This recipe will make 2 small loaves or 2 dozen regular size muffins.
If baking a loaf, you'll need to bake it for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick can be inserted and comes out clean.

title: spicy thai beef salad(waterfall beef)
directions: In blender combine chilies, sugar, lime juice, garlic, peanuts and cilantro to taste.
Stir-fry beef in oil.
Sprinkle liberally with black pepper.
Toss lettuce, onion and scallions.
Add beef and sauce.
Garnish with cilantro.

title: reese cup balls
directions: Mix together confectioners sugar, butter and peanut butter, then chill for one and one half hours.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax over double boiler.
Shape into round balls and roll in chocolate chips.
Place on wax paper.

title: crumble cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix 1 egg and butter with dry cake mix.
Spread in 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.

title: parmesan broiled tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in half crosswise and brush with melted butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Broil 6 inches from heat 5 to 7 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: spiced oyster crackers
directions: Mix warm oil, ranch dressing, spices in covered container and shake well. Drizzle over crackers. Stir slowly, coating crackers well.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix soft dough.
Roll out, cut donuts.
Bake in hot grease.

title: onion soup gratin'ee
directions: Saute onions sliced thinly with garlic in butter until clear. Salt and pepper.
Sprinkle onions with flour and continue stirring.
Add liquid, bay leaf and thyme.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes in a 2-quart saucepan.
When ready to serve, float dried bread on soup and sprinkle on grated cheese.
A nice touch is to put soup in ovenproof dishes and after bread and cheese are added, place in hot oven (450°) until bubbly hot and golden brown.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: In a large bowl, combine rice and 3/4 cup water. Cover with plastic wrap with a section turned back to vent. Cook in microwave on High until water boils, about 2 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand, covered, about 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown wings one layer at a time at 300°.
Remove from pan as they brown.
Drain off oil and add the rest of the ingredients. Bring to boil and stir for 5 minutes on 250°, stirring constantly. Add wings and simmer 15 minutes, covered.
Remove chicken to serving dish and serve over rice.

title: elbert's baked beef stew
directions: Cut up roast.
Brown in butter for about 5 minutes.
Put in pan.
Add onions, celery, carrots, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Add brown sugar and tapioca.
Put gravy mix in 1 cup water.
Heat to a boil and pour over other ingredients.
Add tomatoes.
Cover with foil and bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: cold veggie pizza
directions: Serve this pizza cold as an appetizer.

title: mel's seafood quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour in pie shell. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean and top is slightly brown.

title: barbecued fish
directions: Make a small baking tray from a double layer of aluminum foil. Pour a generous layer of Italian dressing into the tray.
Place fish in tray and coat top layer with more Italian dressing.
Add any spices and vegetables you would like to tray.
Place in preheated barbecue on high (cover closed) for approximately 10 minutes or until flaky.
Remove from heat and enjoy!

title: marilyn's green chili quiche
directions: Into pie crust put cubed cheeses, onion and green chilies. In a mixing bowl, whisk eggs, milk, marjoram and salt.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
This is a great brunch dish.

title: e-z cookies
directions: Mix all but M&M's.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Put M&M's on top and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: spaghetti all'aglio e olio(spaghetti with garlic and oil)
directions: Cook spaghetti in plenty of boiling, salted water, with a dash of olive oil.
Heat olive oil with cloves of garlic but do not let the garlic brown.
Warm oil gently to release the flavor of the garlic.
When spaghetti is cooked, drain it and transfer to a warm serving bowl.
Pour over the oil and garlic and toss the spaghetti well.
Serve immediately.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain completely.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form into small balls.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°. Spray pan first with Pam.

title: cocktail cream puffs(for dessert or appetizers)
directions: Mix flour and salt that has been sifted into small bowl; set aside.
Combine butter and boiling water in medium saucepan.
Keep over low heat until butter is melted.
Add flour all at one time and stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball and leaves the side of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add unbeaten eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Continue beating until a thick dough is formed.
Drop by small teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes 2 inches apart in 425°
oven.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.
Cut off tops to fill when cool.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy time squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add lemon juice.
Slowly add flour, mixing well.
Pour batter into greased cookie sheet and mark off into squares.
Put a tablespoon of pie filling in each square.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top when cool.

title: green onion salad dressing
directions: Mix for 2 minutes in blender.
Add 3 cups salad oil and mix for 5 minutes longer.

title: oatmeal banana nut bread
directions: Combine shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Add bananas and mix well. Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add with oats to creamed mixture. Stir in nuts and flavoring.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: banana bread(guatemalan banana bread)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients; beat 30 seconds.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean (9-inch pan, 70 to 80 minutes, 8-inch loaves, 55 to 60 minutes).
Loosen sides of loaf from pan; remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.
To store, wrap and refrigerate no longer than a week.

title: easy cream cheese dessert
directions: Unroll first package of crescent rolls and lay in bottom of pan (use ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan).
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and spoon over rolls.
Unroll second package of crescent rolls and place on top.
Melt margarine and pour over mixture. Sprinkle top with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except tomatoes, and refrigerate over night. The next day, (since seasonings drain to the bottom) mix well. Then add tomatoes, cut up.
Can be served on lettuce leaves or as a side dish. Makes a good buffet dish.
OPTIONAL: Can add cut up fresh mushrooms, green or red peppers, chunks of chicken or tuna, celery, other cheeses, etc.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients with electric mixer.
Form ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Decorate with parsley and cherries.
Prepare 24 hours ahead.
Freezes well, too!

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots, but not until they fall apart.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 1 day before serving.

title: orange-honey baked chicken(no fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In baking dish, mix the orange juice concentrate, lemon juice, 2 tablespoons honey, orange peel and ginger.
Add chicken pieces, coating both sides.
Let chicken marinate, if time permits, 10 minutes.
Bake chicken, uncovered, at 400° for 8 minutes.
Baste with pan juices.
Bake 8 minutes more. Baste again.
Glaze chicken with mixture of marmalade and remaining 1 tablespoon honey.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes longer until done.
Pour juice over chicken to serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Scald milk in top of double boiler.
Combine sugar, flour and cocoa in a bowl; add enough of hot milk to make paste.
Return to double boiler and stir until thickened.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Add small amount of hot mixture to the 3 well beaten egg yolks.
Mix well and return to boiler.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Drain.
Combine milk, soup and cream cheese together.
Add salt, catsup and meat.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until biscuits are browned.

title: great grandma's scotch shortbread
directions: Cream butter well until almost like whipped cream.
Mix dry ingredients together and add slowly to butter.
I use the mixer as long as possible, then use hands.
Mold into long square logs and refrigerate at least overnight.
Let warm up enough to slice. Place on cookie sheet.
Put holes in top with fork or tenderizer hammer.
Bake at 275° for about 15 minutes.
Don't overbrown.

title: spicy maple coffee ring
directions: Combine dry ingredients with the liquid contents; stir only enough to moisten.
Do not overmix.
Grease small Bundt pans or cupcake pans.
Pour ingredients into the preferred pans.
Preheat the oven to 375° and bake for 15 minutes.

title: smoke chicken
directions: Dissolve Tender Quick in water.
Soak cut up chicken parts for 2 days.
Drain water off
and
rub liquid smoke into meat.
Let set overnight.
No more seasoning is needed.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix together oleo, brown sugar, flour and chopped nuts.
Mix with fingers and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until light golden brown. Watch carefully and stir occasionally. Take out 1/2 cup.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil the water, cocoa and shortening.
Pour over the flour and sugar (combined).
Add the buttermilk.
Add the eggs; beat until smooth.
Add the soda, cinnamon, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in a 12 x 15-inch pan.

title: jello pie
directions: Bring to boil and pour into 1 large can evaporated chilled milk that has been whipped.
Use vanilla wafers for pie crust. Pour in crust and chill.
You can add chopped bananas or pineapple.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding a little
milk,
if
necessary. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Grease pot before pouring in.
Use 1/2 onions while cooking and crumble other half on top when ready to serve.
Cook for 4 hours on high or 6 to 8 hours on low.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: potato and onion pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter in a large bowl.
In
a 10-inch skillet, melt butter over medium heat until foamy, not brown. Drop 1/2 cupfuls of the potato mixture several inches apart into hot butter.
Cook 3 minutes on each side until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm.
Makes 12.
Serve with sour cream and applesauce.

title: tuna macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni, rinse noodles.
Combine tuna, macaroni and white sauce in baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and cheese.
Dress up with cheese strips and pimento, if desired.

title: tuna terrific
directions: Flake tuna in large bowl.
Add and mix well remaining ingredients.
Spoon onto bed of lettuce leaves with tomato slices. Makes 4 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion until tender in about 2 cups water. Stir in soups, milk and water.
Lightly mash potatoes as stirring. Add salt and pepper.
Serve with parsley flakes and bacon sprinkled atop of each bowl and plenty of crackers.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving size pieces.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Coat with flour.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle steak with onion soup mix and bell pepper.
Mix tomato sauce and water in a small bowl.
Pour over steak.
Seal with foil.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: easy cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and onions in oil. Drain off excess oil. Lightly grease casserole dish. Line with chopped cabbage (alternating beef and onion mixture with cabbage and beef). Top with salt and pepper to taste and then add soup. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add salt, pepper and 1/2 cup of cheese on top, if preferred.
Cook at 350° until golden brown.

title: tangy baked ham
directions: Drench ham with Pepsi. Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Mix brown sugar and sauce; spread on ham. Return to oven and bake 30 minutes longer or until glaze has cooked into ham.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix the eggs, oil, sugar and pumpkin in order given, then add the flour, soda, allspice, cloves, baking powder, salt, ginger and cinnamon.
Mix well. Pour into a greased 15 1/2 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool well.
Frost.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: On stove, combine flour and sugar, then add boiling water, stirring constantly.
Add milk and cook until mixture thickens, stirring often.
Separate eggs, saving whites for meringue.
Add one yolk at a time, stirring until mixture is thick and sheets from spoon.
Add butter, lemon juice and rind; stir, then after cool, pour into baked pie shell.

title: candy bars
directions: Melt chocolate and add raisins and peanuts.
Spoon mixture on wax paper in 4 bars.
Chill until firm.

title: salsa
directions: Mix and simmer for 1 hour.
Add 4 tablespoons cornstarch dissolved in 1/2 cup water and cook for 10 more minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Place fresh dill (couple of sprigs) in bottom of quart jar. Closely pack cucumbers in jars.
Heat vinegar, water, salt and all spices and green pepper to a full boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over cucumbers in jars.
Reserve any remaining solution.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Soak poppy seed in amount of liquid the white cake mix calls for, substituting milk for water.
Then make according to box directions.
Top with frosting.

title: fanny farmer fudge
directions: Over medium heat, cook milk and sugar to boil.
Stir for 15 minutes.
Take off heat, add butter and chips and blend together. Walnuts optional. Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and let cool.

title: no-egg pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all
ingredients
and
pour into a single crust pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: coffee liqueur
directions: Bring water and sugar to a rolling boil and boil for 20 minutes.
Add coffee to 1 cup of boiling water and mix into the sugar water.
Add the vanilla and vodka; cool.
Place in a bottle or container and let sit for 1 month, turning frequently.
The liqueur needs to set for at least 1 month; more time just makes it better.

title: robbie's peanut butter bars
directions: Mix
Karo and sugar and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut
butter.
Stir
until
peanut butter melts and is well blended.

title: steamed german brown bread
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Stir in milk.
Add the shortening, molasses and soda mixture.
Place in 1 large or 2 small greased and floured bread pans.
Cover with similar pans.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes to 2 hours in 350° oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: With cheeses at room temperature, mix all ingredients thoroughly and then form ball.
Chill 45 minutes.
Roll in finely chopped nuts.
For well-blended flavors, refrigerate 24 hours.

title: chicken parmes-anna
directions: In large saucepan, heat olive oil.
Saute the garlic, onion, parsley, basil and oregano for 5 minutes.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid and chop into 1/2-inch chunks.
Add tomatoes and liquid to saucepan; simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add marinade from artichokes and wine; simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Coarsely chop artichokes and add to sauce; simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.

title: hearty minestrone
directions: Heat a stockpot over medium-high heat. Place ground beef in stockpot. Cook until browned and crumbly.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; cover and chill. Garnish if desired with avocado slice and fresh cilantro.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 6 cups.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Mix together the creamed corn, egg, corn meal and garlic salt. Set aside.
Mix together the cheese, chiles and butter.
Set aside.

title: m&m goodies
directions: Melt
margarine
in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add graham crackers. Pour
Eagle
Brand milk over crackers.
Sprinkle coconut over the M&M's
and
then nuts; press firmly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: green pea salad
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper and let cool.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve 2 to 3 days after making.

title: "plains special" cheese ring
directions: Mix; mold with hands into desired shape (I mold
into a ring); place in refrigerator until chilled.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, cheese and milk; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, except lettuce.
Mix lightly and chill several hours.
Serve on lettuce.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 400° until done (9 to 12 minutes).

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and add these to the other ingredients.
Mix well in greased and floured 2 loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: crazy rolls
directions: Butter pan; place frozen biscuits in a single layer.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over top of frozen biscuits.
Bring butter and brown sugar to a boil and drizzle over the top of biscuits while hot.
Add nuts and cover with wax paper.
Let them set all night.

title: chicken in the garden
directions: Combine chicken, vegetables, soup, milk and 1 cup onion rings in 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Uncover and top with remaining onion rings.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Combine all ingredients; add milk if too thick.
Cook until shrimp are pink.
Season to taste.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water; mix well.
Stir in flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add sugar, oil and eggs; mix well.
Add carrots, pineapple and nuts; blend thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a tube pan.

title: skillet pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in slow cooker or skillet.
Add salt and pepper.
Spoon soup over chops.
Add enough water to cover chops. Cook in slow cooker about 2 hours.
If using skillet, cook until tender.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes since it makes its own gravy.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Cook wild rice in 1 1/2 cups water for 50 to 60 minutes. Saute onion in butter until tender; add water, milk and soup. Bring this mixture to a simmer while adding chunks of Velveeta. When creamy, add wild rice and serve.

title: crepes suzette
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add flour and beat until smooth.
Add shortening.

title: catfish with salsa
directions: Salt and pepper fillets.
Top each with 2 tablespoons of salsa, 1 ring each of bell pepper and onion.
Wrap each fillet in heavy-duty tinfoil.
Put catfish wrapped in tinfoil on charcoal grill over hot coals and cook 30 to 50 minutes, depending on heat of grill.
Spray foil lightly with Pam before putting fish on it. On our grill they cooked in 30 minutes and were delicious.

title: cheesy chicken wings
directions: Mix together the bread crumbs, cheese, basil, oregano and garlic salt.
Dip wings into margarine, then into bread crumb mixture.
Place in baking dish; bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: golden brown party puffs
directions: Trim all crusts from bread.
Cut into 3/4-inch cubes.
Melt two cheeses and butter together over low heat.
Cool slightly. Add beaten egg whites.
Dip bread cubes into mixture until well coated.
Place on buttered cookie sheets.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours or as long as overnight.
Preheat oven to 400°. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes about 48 puffs.

title: skillet chocolate pie
directions: Add all ingredients and cook until reasonably thick.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with beaten egg whites from two eggs.
Brown meringue in oven at 350°.

title: mexican goupe
directions: Mix soups, Ro-Tel and browned meat.
Layer 3 tortillas in an oblong baking dish, soup mixture, cheese, 3 more tortillas, soup mixture and cheese.
Heat in oven or microwave until cheese melts.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Add flour, soda and spices.
Fold in mashed prunes.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: vanilla cupcakes
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour and milk until soupy.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage coarsely.
Cook in boiling water until tender; drain.
Add eggs, margarine and cracker crumbs.
Mix well and spread in a shallow, greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until browned.
Brown 1 to 1 1/2 cups large cracker pieces in melted margarine in frying pan, stirring until golden brown.
Spoon over top of cabbage before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix salt and flour.
Whisk together oil and water; pour into flour mixture and stir with fork until blended.
Form into a ball and roll between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Makes 1 pie crust (9-inch); 125 calories per serving.

title: chicken chili
directions: Note:
Chicken sausage can be found at delicatessen.
Turkey sausage and ground turkey may be substituted.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Add sugar, strawberries and eggs.
Stir in oil and mix well.
Pour into 3 well-greased 1-pound coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk; cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Cool and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into yolks; immediately return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla. Add 1 cup of coconut.
Pour into cooled baked pastry shell.
Top with meringue.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup of coconut.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Layer dish with stuffing mix, chicken and soups and cheese and start over with another layer.
Always end up with the last layer being stuffing mix.

title: tiny hot meat balls no. 2
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into tiny balls.
Brown on all sides in butter.
Add a little hot water, bouillon or meat stock to balls and keep hot in chafing dish or top of double boiler while being served.
Serve with picks.
We like sweet and sour sauce over the meat balls.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Put in casserole bowl.
Crush crackers.
Mix 1 tablespoon butter or margarine in crackers and spread over top of casserole.
Bake until it bubbles.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Tear the bread into chunks (the size of golf balls).
Place in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour warm sauce over and let raise. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let set 10 to 15 minutes.
Invert on platter.

title: strawberry sour cream nut bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Cream sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, then add sour cream just until moistened.
Fold in berries and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan and bake for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: texas straw hats
directions: Brown meat
and mix with your choice of seasonings.
On a plate, put
a
handful of Fritos and a scoop of meat on top. Sprinkle with cheese, onions and a dash of hot sauce.

title: malmstrom swedish pancakes
directions: Beat all together (by hand or blender) until smooth and well blended.
Pour small amount into hot oiled pan.
Shake pan (or tilt) quickly so that batter covers pan thinly and evenly (large burner at "7").
Cook until golden brown on both sides.
Serve while hot, rolled up into tight log (buttered or jellied).
These are very good if you add just a touch of cinnamon and nutmeg to batter.
(Jeremy Coates loves these.)

title: honey spiced chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Combine honey, salt, butter, mustard and curry powder.
Mix well.
Dip chicken pieces in sauce and place chicken skin side up in a roasting pan.
Bake 1 hour at 375 degrees.
Baste occasionally with remaining sauce.
Serve over rice if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
In another large bowl, beat eggs until light yellow.
Add sugar and oil slowly, continue to beat.
Combine buttermilk, zucchini, vanilla and orange peel.
Add buttermilk mixture alternately with flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
While hot, drizzle with orange glaze.

title: pate with pistachios
directions: Preheat oven to 425.
Cut pork and veal into 1 inch cubes. Cut ham into 1/2 inch cubes.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients.	Add
eggs
and pumpkin.
Grease cookie sheet pan.	Line with waxed paper.	Spread mixture over waxed paper.
Sprinkle
with chopped nuts (if desired).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Use an oblong baking pan.
Line baking pan with blueberries. On top of blueberries dump crushed pineapple and juice and cake mix.
Pat down dry mix.
Add nuts and pat down over mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until light brown.
Cool and cut into squares.
Serve plain or with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: seasoned pork roast
directions: Mix together garlic salt and black pepper.
Rub on pork roast. Roast in a 350° oven for 40 minutes per pound.
Baste the last 30 minutes with honey, prepared horseradish and ground ginger.

title: greek meat balls
directions: Mix beef, onion and seasonings.
Dip bread into milk and break into small pieces.
Pour balance of milk into meat; mix with bread. Mix thoroughly.
Shape into small balls, about 2-inches in length. Roll meat balls into flour and fry in hot oil (about 1/2-inch in depth), until done on both sides.
Turn over once.

title: sugar free applesauce raisin cake
directions: Place water and raisins in saucepan; bring to a boil and simmer until all liquid is absorbed. Set aside to cool. Mix all dry ingredients. Whip eggs slightly and add with rest of ingredients to dry ingredients. If raisins are cool, add. Cook in preheated
350° oven until toothpick in the middle comes out clean. I cook mine in a loaf pan.

title: yogurt egg salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and use fork to blend lightly.
Serve on lettuce or in sandwiches.
Serves 2.

title: wally's beans
directions: Bring to rolling boil.
Turn down to simmer; cook 5 hours until juice is thick.

title: super salad
directions: Combine fruits; add pudding mix and marshmallows.
Let stand in refrigerator for several hours.
Fold in Cool Whip 1 hour or more before serving.
If using larger portions, double pudding mix. Also, I have used lemon pudding mix.
Gives a decided lemon flavor.

title: oriental beef with peppers
directions: Heat pan; add oil and garlic. When garlic turns brown, remove from heat. Add beef and fry a few minutes (2 to 4) or until meat slices are no longer red. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Add bouillon, soy sauce and remaining ingredients. Cook until tender.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and blend into batter alternately with milk and vanilla. Do not overmix.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake in oven 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 13-inch loaf pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper with shrimp.
Add tomatoes.
Add garlic, salt and pepper to taste and add chili powder.
Cook for 20 minutes and serve over white rice.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn from cob and mix with red and green peppers, cabbage and onions.
Heat 2 cups vinegar to boiling.
Add sugar, salt, mustard, flour and turmeric.
Add rest of vinegar.
Boil until slightly thick.
Add vegetables.
Stir until well blended.
Cook slowly for 1/2 hour.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Cut up carrots and cook until tender.
Chop onion and pepper. Heat the tomato soup, vinegar, sugar, mustard and soy sauce.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.
Will keep for 3 to 4 weeks.

title: terry bradshaw's smoke chicken
directions: You will need 10 to 15 hickory wood chips.

title: broken glass torte
directions: Dissolve separately, each box of gelatin with 1/2 cup boiling water and pour into ice cube trays.
Freeze overnight.
The next day, remove from freezer and cut each cube into 1/2 in cubes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Make a well in center; add oil, water and pumpkin, mix well.
Stir in walnuts. Pour
into
x
5-inch loaf pans (2).
Bake for 60 minutes. May be served with whipped cream or whipped topping.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Remove meat
from bones.
Mix all liquids together.
Put layer of chicken,
chips,
cheese and onions.
Pour liquid over this. Make 2 layers.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: harvest cake
directions: Beat sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Mix flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Will be a heavy dough.
May need to mix with fingers.
Add nuts and diced apples.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: italian potato casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage until no longer pink and drain. Place in greased 9-inch square baking dish. Top with potatoes. In the same skillet, saute onion, green pepper and garlic in oil for 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Stir in mushrooms, tomatoes, olives, basil, salt and pepper. Spoon over potatoes to within 1-inch of edge of dish. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and parsley on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until top is lightly browned. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: frosty raspberry gelatin mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Whip cream cheese and mayonnaise until fluffy.
Slowly blend in cranberry sauce, gelatin mixture and wine.
Stir in pineapple; chill until mixture begins to set.
Fold in whipped cream.
Sprinkle reserved juice over apple and bananas; fold into gelatin mixture.
Pour into six 1-cup molds; chill until firm. Unmold on lettuce-lined plates.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cocoa peanut squares
directions: Have ingredients measured.
Combine syrup and sugar in a 3 quart saucepan. cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently until mixture bubbles around edges of pan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until completely mixed.
Add cocoa Krispies, stirring until coated with syrup mixture.
Press into greased 8 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in the hot milk, mixing well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until knife inserted just off center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: apple crisp(microwave)
directions: Place apple slices in an 8 x 8-inch glass dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Cut butter into brown sugar; add oats, flour and salt.
Pat topping over apples.
Microwave 15 minutes at High. Turn dish 1/4 turn every 5 minutes.
Can double recipe and put in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Microwave 20 minutes on High.

title: taco salad
directions: On plate, layer lettuce, tomato, tortilla chips, chili and grated cheese in that order. Serve with sour cream and picante sauce.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Bring
water,
sugar and spices to a boil.
Remove from heat and
add lemons and juices.
Remove cloves and cinnamon. Serve hot.
Yields 15 to 18 servings.

title: speedy beefburgers
directions: Combine egg, cracker crumbs, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, onion powder, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef and mix well. Shape meat mixture into 6 patties.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Add remaining water. Add pineapple and pour in a large container.
Let set.
When Jell-O layer is almost set, sprinkle with miniature marshmallows. Add water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup (in a small saucepan). Add sugar, flour and eggs.
Mix well and cook until thick.
Cool.

title: broccoli potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange potatoes on bottom and up sides of 8 x 12-inch casserole.
Bake uncovered for 10 minutes.
Brown vegetable protein.
Add broccoli and 1/2 can onions and tomatoes into potato shell.
Combine soup, milk, 1/2 cup cheese and seasonings.
Pour this over casserole.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 2 to 3 minutes longer.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325° and grease and flour 9 x 9-inch pan.
Put the peeled and chopped apples, sugar and egg in a large mixing bowl.
Mix flour, soda and spices and sift gradually into apple mixture along with the raisins.
Add vanilla and cooking oil. Put in prepared pan and bake for 1 hour.

title: six week muffins
directions: Place 1 cup cereal in a large bowl.
Pour boiling water over bran.
Stir in margarine and set aside.
Combine remaining bran with sugar, eggs and buttermilk.
Sift flour with soda, salt and cinnamon.
Combine all ingredients, blending well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
When ready to bake, grease muffin tins and fill 2/3 full with batter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: fern's special peanut butter cookies
directions: Put sugars, syrup and vanilla in saucepan and bring to a boil. Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add cereal and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: mom's lemon bundt cake
directions: Combine and beat all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour into a Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
(Do not over bake.)

title: aunt carmen's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Chop and saute vegetable with 1/4 of Good Seasons, garlic and black pepper.
Add vegetables and chopped artichokes to pasta.
Add envelope of Good Seasons and salad dressing.
Mix well.
Add cheeses; stir again.
Chill before serving.

title: shoney's hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in top of double boiler. Add sugar a little at a time. Add the salt and
milk, stirring as you pour. Continue stirring until it becomes glossy.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground meat.
Saute with chopped onion.
Add all the other ingredients to the meat and onion in a large pan.
Cook, covered, for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: sugar free cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place water and raisins in saucepan and cook until water has evaporated.
Cool 10 minutes.
Add applesauce, eggs, Sweet 'N Low and oil.
Blend well and add flour, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rancho beans
directions: Bake in moderate 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar together.
Place in bottom of pie crust.
Drain pineapple and place on cream cheese mixture.
Slice bananas over pineapples.
Add cool whip in top. Add nuts and cherries on top of cool whip, if desired.

title: italian chicken casserole
directions: Cut up chicken breasts in small pieces.
Beat up eggs.
Put chicken in eggs and let set for 1 hour.
Dip chicken in bread crumbs; brown on both sides, using margarine.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese, broth and mushrooms.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Uncover for the last 10 minutes.

title: quick chicken and pasta
directions: Prepare linguine (or your favorite pasta) according to directions on package.
Cut chicken breast strips into bite size pieces.
Brown in skillet with margarine.
Add tomatoes and cream of mushroom soup; stir until mixed well.
Turn fire to low and simmer until chicken is tender, stirring often.
Serve over pasta.

title: turtle cake
directions: Combine cake mix, water, eggs and butter; blend until smooth. Pour 1/2 batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels with evaporated milk over low heat.
Pour over cake when removed from oven.
(Do not spread to edges.) Sprinkle chips over caramel, then nuts.
Pour remaining batter over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Melt caramels while cake bakes.

title: kids favorite fudge
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, stir margarine, sugar and evaporated milk until melted.
Add marshmallows, stirring constantly.
When mixture begins to bubble, stop stirring and lower heat to very low.
Allow to gently bubble for 5 minutes. Add vanilla and remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted. Pour into greased 8-inch pan.
Set for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Add chicken and pimento. Mix other ingredients with half of the cheese; blend.
Pour into baking dish and add remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
This can be frozen before baking.
A very easy and quick casserole.
Can be kept in freezer, making a nice meal for unexpected guests.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Brown pork chops in oil in skillet until brown.
Arrange potatoes in 2 1/2-quart casserole or skillet you have browned chops in.
Mix soup, milk and onion; pour over potatoes.
Place pork chops on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: best ever banana muffins
directions: Mash bananas.
Add sugar and slightly beaten egg.
Add melted butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: wild rice and turkey casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Mix together undiluted soup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and mushrooms.
Then add rice and mix.
Into well-greased baking dish, spoon 1/2 of rice mixture, then 1/2 of turkey.
Mix bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook soup bones in water with meat that has been browned for 2 hours in a slow oven. Add crushed tomatoes and soda and cook on fast boil for 15 minutes. Add cabbage, carrots, celery and potatoes.
Add onions that have been browned in butter.
Continue to boil. Add the rosamarina and continue to cook for about 40 minutes. Add seasoning the last 15 minutes of the 40 minutes. Remove cabbage and serve to the crowd.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in buttered 8 x 12-inch pan.
Mix together flour, sugar, butter, oats and cinnamon until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Pour half of the batter into greased and floured oblong pan and bake at 350° until done.
Melt candies in milk.
Pour over baked half of cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans. Pour on rest of batter and bake until done.

title: stir fry chicken and pasta
directions: Cook stir-fry according to directions.
Boil spaghetti, drain and then toss lightly with butter, salt and pepper.
Set aside. When both are cooked, mix together.
Serve with slice of garlic bread.

title: norwegian style pickles
directions: Mix together vinegar, sugar, celery seed and garlic.
Shake well in jug.
Pour over cucumbers, peppers and onion.
Let stand. Keep in refrigerator.

title: potato buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Measure flour into large bowl.
Mix all other ingredients; add yeast mixture and pour over flour.
Mix good and knead.
Let rise.
Punch down in bowl, take approximately 1/4 cup portions rolling in your hands to form a ball and place on cookie sheet.
Bake on middle shelf at 350° for 10 minutes or until nicely browned.
Yields approximately 2 dozen.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown beef; pour off drippings and blend in gravy mix, garlic, salt, water and rice.
Bring to boil; reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in peas.
Cook until rice is tender.
Serve with gravy sauce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant that has been peeled and cut in cubes until tender. Cook squash until tender. Saute chopped onion in 1/2 stick margarine until clear. Add eggplant, squash, onion and herb stuffing. Combine soup, egg, milk, pepper and half of the cheese. Mix.
Pour soup over vegetable that has been placed in greased casserole dish. Sprinkle remainder of cheese on top. Cover top with cracker crumbs and dot with remainder of margarine.
Bake 40 minutes in a 2-quart casserole dish 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: blue cheese spread
directions: In a large bowl combine cream cheese, Blue cheese and milk; beat until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients and mix until combined. Shape into ball or wreath; sprinkle tops and sides with dried parsley.
Use extra pimento to garnish if you wish.
Chill until served.
(Great to make ahead.)
Serve with crackers or bread rounds.

title: banana pickles
directions: Peel and seed cucumbers.
This is a good recipe for larger cucumbers.
Pack them in jars.
Boil rest of ingredients and pour over cucumbers in jars.
Cold pack for 5 minutes.

title: black bean chili with rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add green pepper, garlic and onion.
Cook and stir until crisp and tender. Stir in beans, tomatoes, ham, oregano, ground cayenne and bay leaf.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve bean mixture over rice.
Serves 4.

title: creamy cheddar dip
directions: In small bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually blend in milk.
Add Cheddar cheese, beating until well blended.
Cover; chill 1 hour.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Press cookie dough out flat to edges of pan.
Cook according to directions on roll of cookie dough.
Take out when lightly brown, let cool completely.
Cream together cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla; then fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cooled cookie (must be completely cool).
Top with sliced strawberries.
Store in refrigerator.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: In large container, combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, spoon 2 to 3 teaspoons into mug and add 1 cup boiling water.
This will make a great gift when presented in an attractive container.

title: four ways to dunk a vegetable
directions: Puree cucumber with 1/2 cup yogurt, then add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: tomato and egg salad
directions: Set tomato stem end down and cut into 8 evenly spaced slices, cutting to within 1/2-inch from the bottom.
(Do not cut all the way through.)
Arrange lettuce on salad plate and place tomato on the lettuce.
Gently spread tomato slices slightly apart and drizzle 1/2 of the dressing over the tomato.
Cut egg slices and put between each tomato slice.
Drizzle with the rest of the dressing.
Garnish with chopped green onions and/or parsley.

title: ooey gooey cake
directions: Mix
butter
and cake mix; add eggs.
Press into bottom of
a greased 12 x 9-inch pan.
Mix softened cream cheese, egg and confectioners sugar; put on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar over top.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight or until firm.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Add sugar, flour, vanilla, cocoa and salt.
Stir in hot tap water (just enough to mix everything well, without lumps).
Cook on low heat.
Add butter; stir.
Add milk and stir; cook for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: gooey peanut butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine the cake mix, egg, and butter and mix well. Pat into a lightly greased 13 x 9 inch baking pan. Prepare filling.

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
At the same time, saute onion and celery until tender in 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Add drained mushrooms. Drain macaroni.
Add soup and stir.
Add tuna, onions and celery. Stir well.
Serve.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 4 layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with your favorite recipe.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add syrup and butter.
Pour over nuts in pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°, then for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.	Stir in peanut butter.	Mix well.
Add Rice Krispies. Stir until well blended.
Press into 13 x 9 pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together over hot, not boiling water, stirring until well blended.
(Can also be melted in microwave on High for about 2 minutes.
Do not overcook.)
Spread over Rice Krispies.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sugared popcorn
directions: Combine in a small bowl popcorn, water and food coloring, if used.
In 3-quart saucepan, melt shortening.
Stir sugar into shortening.
Add popcorn and water to this.
Stir with wooden spoon constantly until popcorn starts to pop.
Cover, shaking constantly.
Pop quickly over high heat.
At the peak of popping, remove from heat to prevent sugar from burning.
Pour onto cookie sheet.
When cool enough to handle, break apart pieces.
Store in sealed container.
Makes approximately 5 cups.

title: pineapple upside-down cups
directions: Place 1 teaspoon of butter or margarine and 1 tablespoon of brown sugar in each of four 10 ounce custard cups.
Arrange a slice of pineapple and a cherry in each cup.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Shape 1 1/2 biscuits into a round circle.
Place on top of pineapple in cups.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, until biscuits are cooked through and golden.

title: chopped ham sandwich
directions: Put cubed cheese, diced celery, minced onion and sliced and diced ham into large bowl.
In small bowl, mix vinegar, sugar and Miracle Whip together, then pour over ingredients in larger bowl. Fill sandwich rolls with mixture.
Wrap sandwiches in foil.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Heat in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: coconut macaroons(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine coconut, flour and baking powder.
Beat egg whites until foamy; add cream of tartar and Sucaryl.
Beat until peaks form.
Fold egg whites into coconut mixture.
Drop onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: congo squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar slowly over heat. Add eggs, flour, chocolate bits and flavoring. When well mixed, pour into two 9 x 9-inch baking pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together in baking dish, uncooked.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 45 minutes. Stir once.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Blend and mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: italian baked spaghetti
directions: Brown beef and onions together.
Add tomato sauce and spices. Simmer for one hour.
Add cooked spaghetti and put in a greased roasting pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves approximately 15.

title: pull apart coffee cake
directions: Melt brown sugar, margarine, cinnamon and vanilla in saucepan; bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Cut each biscuit into 1/4 pieces. Line bottom of Bundt pan with 1 can of biscuits.
Pour 1/3 of sauce and repeat twice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dannon low-fat brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan).
Combine brownie mix, yogurt, egg whites (or substitute) and vanilla in a bowl.
Mix well.
Batter will be very thick.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 22 to 24 minutes or 32 to 34 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch pan or 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool before cutting.
Makes 24 servings.

title: corn and spinach biscuits
directions: About 45 minutes before serving or early in day:
Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
With pastry blender or two knives used scissor-fashion, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl, blend all ingredients together and put in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugar and beat until smooth. Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda; add alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and nuts. Fold in egg whites.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool; frost with cream cheese frosting.
If using self-rising flour, omit soda.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt; add pineapple.
Cook until clear and thickened.
Add beaten yolks.
Cook 1 minute.
Cool. Add lemon juice.
Pour into baked shell.
Top with meringue made by folding 4 tablespoons sugar into stiffly beaten egg whites. Brown in a 325° oven.

title: owens sausage deep fried cheese grits
directions: Bring broth to a boil in large saucepan; add salt and grits. Return to a boil, reduce heat and continue to cook for 5 minutes. In another pan, saute onion and bell pepper in margarine until onion is transparent; set aside.
Add cheese to grits until all cheese is melted and incorporated.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir to mix.

title: corn "pudding"
directions: Mix the corns and eggs together, then add sugar, cornstarch, seasoned salt and dried onion to mixture.
Then stir in milk and melted margarine.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 400°, stirring once.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in skillet.
When cooled, crumble in same pan with drippings.
Add 1 quart tomatoes, onion, parsley and sugar until boiling.
Add bread (enough until not too runny).

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onion and drain well.
Cut lettuce into bite size pieces.
Mix ketchup and mayonnaise together in a separate bowl.
Then combine all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour in ketchup and mayonnaise mixture and mix well.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and peanut butter.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Take out and melt chocolate chips.
When cool, ice with combined powdered sugar, peanut butter and milk.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Combine pears, sugar and pecans and let set for 1 hour, stirring often.
Add flour,
nutmeg,
cinnamon, salt and soda. Add oil, vanilla and eggs.
Do
not use mixer.
Pour into tube pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Allow to cool in pan for 15 to 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix all together real good. Put in baking dish. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cherry hum mum
directions: Mix melted butter in cracker crumbs.
Put 3/4 of the crumb mixture in pan 9 x 12-inch size.
Put cherry pie filling on crumb mixture.
Beat milk, cream cheese, Dream Whip, sugar and 1 teaspoon flour.
Pour over the pie filling and chill.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a 2 quart glass casserole dish, combine first 5 ingredients.
Cover and microwave on high for 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except the shrimp.
Cook an additional 5 minutes.
Stir mixture and add cooked shrimp.
Cover and cook an additional 6-7 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Bring to a boil the pineapple, sugar and flour. Remove from heat; add jello.
Drain cherries and add.
Let cool 10 minutes or longer. Add pecans and bananas (quarter bananas lengthwise and slice).
Pour in baked pie shells. Cover with Saran Wrap. Chill overnight. Spread
Cool Whip over pies when ready to serve.
Makes 3 small pies or 2 large.

title: alex's casserole
directions: First, peel and boil potatoes to mash. Brown hamburger, salt and pepper to taste. Drain off grease. Add the can of tomato soup to the browned meat. Drain and add the green beans. Mix well; let simmer. When the potatoes are ready, mash with butter, salt and pepper to taste. Put hamburger mixture in a baking dish. Spread mashed potatoes on top. Sprinkle grated cheese over the potatoes. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to a boil over medium heat sugar, margarine and milk. Boil 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cake flour
directions: Put cornstarch in measuring cup, then fill remainder of cup with all-purpose flour.
Sift together 3 times.
One cup of this is equal to 1 cup sifted cake flour.

title: beef or venison jerky
directions: Mix the
last
ingredients together in a large bowl. Add the meat and
mix
real
well,
so
every piece of meat is coated. Put into a closed container and marinate for 48 hours in refrigerator.
After 48 hours, line the bottom of your oven with foil.
Spray oven racks with Pam cooking spray.
Lay meat slices on racks and
turn oven to 125° and cook for 4 hours or until it looks
dry.
Take
out,
cool
and
refrigerate
in a Ziploc bag.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Debone and remove skin from chicken.
Dredge the chicken pieces in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in some olive oil, just until onions are clear (not browned).
Remove from pan and deglaze the pan with white wine. Pour the wine over the onion and garlic.

title: potatoes and chicken santa fe
directions: Microwave potatoes 8 to 10 minutes, until tender; cut in 3/4-inch cubes.
Cube chicken and brown in skillet with oil.
Add potatoes; toss until potatoes are slightly browned.
Add salsa and corn; toss until heated through.
Serves 4.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Cook all ingredients in saucepan until it thickens.
Remove from stove and cool.
Spread over baked cake.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes.
Place in 2-quart baking dish with salt and pepper.
Place pork chops on potatoes.
Dilute mushroom soup. Pour over chops and potatoes.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and finish baking until chops are cooked to desired tenderness.

title: edylene mcgill's egg rolls
directions: Chop finely all together (except wrappers).
Roll in wonton wrapper.
Fry in hot oil, 2 or 3 minutes.
May also be baked or microwaved.
Quantity depends on how full you want the rolls to be.

title: spoon bread
directions: Pour boiling water over cornmeal.
Stir and let cool.
Add butter and egg yolks.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Stir in buttermilk.
Combine salt, sugar, baking powder and soda.
Add to cornmeal mixture.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Fold into cornmeal mixture.
Pour into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes until set at 350°.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat all ingredients in blender for a few seconds.
Pour into a greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Cool before cutting.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt, butter and vanilla; mix well.
Add eggs.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over all.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes. When cool, you may top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: twice baked cheese potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; dry and pierce with fork.
Do not wrap in foil.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour.
When potatoes are done, melt butter in skillet and saute onions until clear.
Halve potatoes lengthwise; scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Mash potatoes and add other ingredients, beating in enough milk to make fluffy consistency.
Fill shells.
Pile high.
Bake at 400° until tops are lightly brown.

title: deep dish chicken pie
directions: Put chicken, soup and broth in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix biscuit mix, butter and milk; spoon evenly over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done and crust is brown.
This is good served over noodles or rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and drain.
Mix with cheese and broccoli until cheese is melted.
Add chicken soup, water chestnuts, milk and soy sauce with buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Flatten biscuits slightly and put mustard on one side.
Wrap biscuit around hot dog, pinching the sides together firmly.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients into crumbs. Remove 1 cup crumbs for topping.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Put in large pan.
Add cut nuts and cut fruit; stir well.
Pour condensed milk over ingredients; stir well.
Will just hold together.
Cake can be packed back into empty cracker box.
You may think it won't all go, but it will. Leave in box overnight before cutting.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice vegetables thinly.
In a buttered 2-quart casserole, place a layer of vegetables.
Mix all dry ingredients together. Add 1/2 of this to first layer.
Also, add 1/2 of cheese (both kinds).
Dot with margarine.
Continue with layers of vegetables, dry ingredients, cheese and margarine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 minutes or so longer.
Will serve 6.
Very good!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Cut into bite size pieces. In casserole dish, combine chicken with rice, soups and 2 cans water Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake in 350 oven for 1 hour.

title: crab mousse
directions: Combine over low heat, cream cheese, mushroom soup, mayonnaise and worcestershire sauce.
Stir until smooth and remove from heat.
In a separate bowl, dissolve 2 envelopes of knox gelatin in cold water.
Add crabmeat and gelatin to pan ingredients and then add celery and onion and stir.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in oblong baking dish.
Combine sugar, flour and milk; pour into dish.
Spoon pie filling on top.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 35 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour 1/2 of cake batter into 8 1/2 x 13-inch greased cake pan and bake 15 minutes.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt; gradually add scalded milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Add small amount to egg yolks; stir into remaining hot mixture.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla and cool slightly.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with meringue made of egg whites and sugar. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Place butter, onion and green pepper in 2-quart glass casserole.
Microwave on Roast for 4 to 5 minutes (until vegetables are partly cooked). Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover with plastic wrap.

title: maple syrup pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine syrup, sugar and butter in saucepan.
Bring to boil, then simmer uncovered for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool slightly.
Place pecans in shell. Mix eggs, vanilla and salt in bowl.
Gradually stir in cooled syrup.
Pour over pecans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until silver knife comes out clean.
Cool.

title: cinnamon apple salad
directions: Stir gelatin, water and red hots until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan and chill until partially set.
When partially set, add walnuts.
In separate bowl, blend cream cheese, milk and mayonnaise.
Swirl cheese mixture into gelatin to achieve a marbled appearance.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Use a big pan.
Mix all ingredients, except soup, together with 1/2 of the broth.
To rest of broth, add mushroom soup.
Pour over dressing.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend well all ingredients.
Chill.
Hollow out pumpernickel roll.
Fill with dip.
Use bread for dipping.

title: tasty asparagus
directions: Blend 3 tablespoons butter with flour in saucepan over low heat.
Add milk and cheese and stir until cheese melts (thin with milk if too thick).
Stir cracker crumbs into 1/2 cup melted butter.
Line 1 1/2-quart casserole with 1/2 of crumb mixture. Alternate layers of asparagus and almonds.
Top with cheese sauce and remaining cracker crumbs mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Using mixer, beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla, oil and grated zucchini.
Mix flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon together.
Add to egg mixture gradually.
Then add nuts.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Slice and serve warm with butter; serve cold with cream cheese or just serve plain.

title: mystery pie
directions: Fold egg whites in Ritz crackers, sugar and pecans.
Then add salt and vanilla.
Pour into buttered pie pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 50 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip and melted Hershey's chocolate.
"Um-um good."

title: pig stew
directions: Place ingredients in slow cooker or crock-pot and cook until tender.
Add other seasonings to your taste.

title: potatoes hungarian
directions: Wash and boil potatoes. Peel and slice potatoes and eggs. Melt butter and sour cream in saucepan.
Put potatoes, onion, eggs, parsley, salt, pepper and bread crumbs in layers in baking dish.
Repeat, ending with crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in oven which has been preheated to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: saucy potatoes
directions: In a sauce pan combine soup and broth, stir in potatoes and cook over medium low heat until mixture just begins to simmer and potatoes are heated through. Yield four servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese per directions. Add mushroom soup, tuna, June peas and bell pepper. Place into baking dish. Cook for 15 minutes at 400°. Add grated cheese and cook until cheese is melted.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix crab, mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Heat soup and gelatine. When soup mixture is cool, add crab mixture, celery and onions. Mix together.
Put in mold and let set.
Unmold and serve with crackers or chips.

title: chocolate macadamia nut pie
directions: Crush wafers in food processor. Combine crumbs with melted butter and press into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Melt chocolate in a double boiler over hot, not boiling water, or in the microwave.
Allow to cool slightly.

title: individual cheesecakes
directions: Cream the cream cheese, then add eggs, sugar and vanilla. Pour into aluminum muffin liners 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Take 1 cup sour cream and 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat and fill.
Bake 5 minutes.
Refrigerate and add favorite topping after chilled.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown rice in 1/2 stick of butter.
Mix all ingredients together and put in square baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: granny's sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar; bring to a boil. Mix margarine, Crisco, water and cocoa. Pour over flour and sugar. Add eggs, vanilla, cinnamon, soda and buttermilk. Bake on greased cookie sheet 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pat into 8-inch square pan, ungreased.
Mix next 6 ingredients together and add coconut and nuts.
Pour over crust.

title: easy eclairs(blue ribbon winner)
directions: Beat all together until smooth.
Spread over cake.
Must refrigerate 24 hours!

title: tourtiere(quebec meat filled pie)
directions: Cook pork and beef until they crumble and begin to brown. Add onions, garlic, salt, spices and herbs. Saute for 3 or 4 minutes. Add potato water and bring to a boil uncovered. Reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes to an hour until liquid is absorbed. Stir often. Remove from heat and stir in chopped potatoes and eggs. Mix until well combined. Chill mixture thoroughly. Fill 2 pastry lined pie plates. Top with pastry and seal edges. Make several slashes in top to let out steam. Bake at 450° in lower 1/3 of oven for 10 minutes. Lower heat to 350° and bake until crust is brown. Cool 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix over heat until sugar and jello are dissolved.
Pour over popped corn.
Butter hands real good and form popcorn balls.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Blend soups and milk in greased casserole.
Stir in meat, vegetable and 2/3 noodles.
Top with remaining noodles.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: eves pudding
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Put in pie dish with sugar and water.
Bake in moderate oven 10 minutes.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Gradually beat in eggs and stir in flour.
Spread this mixture over hot apples.
Return to oven for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle over with sugar before serving.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine gelatin, 1/2 cup sugar, spices and salt. Stir in evaporated milk and beaten egg yolks.
Cook and stir over low heat until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add pumpkin. Chill, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks, gradually adding remaining 1/4 cup sugar. Continue to beat until they hold a soft peak.
Fold in pumpkin mixture and spoon into the pie shell.
Chill until firm and garnish with whipped cream and/or raisins which have been soaked in rum.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together. Let marinate 1 hour.

title: crumbled top apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt into a bowl. Add shortening, egg, apples and milk.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: "chicken"
directions: Mix together the soups and rice.
Put in bottom of casserole dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice mixture.
Cover and bake.
When chicken is done, uncover and cook to brown the chicken.

title: caipirinha
directions: Mix the sugar and the lime in a small pitcher and crush it. Add "Cachaca" or vodka and mix.
Add ice.
Serve.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Mix grated cheese and sausage.
Add Bisquick mix, a little at a time, until cheese and sausage mix.
Knead until blended.
Set aside.
Stuff peppers with cheese.
Take small amount of mixture and pat like pancake and wrap pepper.
Dip in egg and then roll in Shake 'n Bake.
Bake in oven at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese, 2 tablespoons butter and milk.
Add chicken, salt, pepper and onion.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles.
Press out perforations.
Spoon 1/2 cup of mixture on center of each.
Pull up four corners, crimp edges and seal. Brush all sides with remaining butter.
Dip in crushed croutons. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Makes 4.

title: west phalian ham with honeydew melon
directions: Cut melon into 12 wedges; remove seeds and rind.
Place wedges on plates or platter.
Lay ham slices over the top.
Garnish with pepper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: clam chowder
directions: Slice up bacon into small pieces, and brown very slowly until golden brown and crunchy in a large stock pot, on low heat.
Remove cooked crisp bacon from pan with slotted spoon and put on paper towels to remove excess grease.
Drain all but 1 Tbsp. of grease from the pan.
To the same pan add the center leafy section of celery chopped fine and 1 sweet onion chopped fine.
Saute till onions are translucent.
Add 10 large potatoes chopped.
Add liquid only from the cans of clams.
Add grated carrots.
Cover and bring to slow simmer.
Cook until tender, about 45 minutes.
Add clams, half and half and 1 qt of whole milk.
Bring to almost a boil.
Add together 2/3 c. milk and 1/3 c. flour and whisk.
Add this mixture to the pan while stirring constantly.
Bring almost to the boiling point again.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add bacon bits and serve.
If you like it thicker add a small amount of corn starch. The thickness will be a bit different every time you make it because of the amount the potatoes break down.
This will freeze well and makes 6 to 7 qts.

title: seven flavoring pound cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine, shortening and sugar until fluffy. Add well beaten eggs.
Alternate flour and milk; beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not turn out of tube pan when done. Add glaze while still hot, in tube pan.

title: play dough(not edible)
directions: Cook over medium heat until it leaves sides of pan.
Knead with hands until smooth.
Store in airtight container.
Will keep for months.

title: quick baked pasta
directions: Bring 4-quarts of water to a boil.
Heat a large frying pan and add the oil, beef and garlic.
Saute until the meat is tender and then drain excess fat.
Add all remaining ingredients except the cheeses.
Simmer the mixture while the pasta cooks until just barely tender.
Drain the pasta and mix it with the sauce.
Pour all into a 3-quart glass rectangular baking dish and top with the cheeses.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until all is bubbly hot.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute butter, celery and onion. Add soup and cheez whiz.

title: potato bacon chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in 3-quart saucepan.
Add onion.
Saute 3 minutes.
Pour off drippings.
Add potatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Gradually stir in soup, sour cream, milk and parsley.
Bring to serving temperature over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Do not boil.
Add cooked bacon just before serving.

title: orange street punch
directions: Add juices and mashed bananas to sugar-water mixture.
Freeze in any plastic jugs.
When ready to use, thaw for 1 hour before serving.
Cut jugs; place partially thawed mixture in a punch bowl.
Add 2 to 3 liters of ginger ale.

title: ten minute chili
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion in heavy pot.
Add sugar, salt and chili powder; stir.
Add tomato juice and beans.
Bring to a boil.

title: ladyfinger cheese cake
directions: Line spring-form pan with ladyfingers on sides and bottom of pan, filling in bottom as much as possible (OK to add smaller pieces to fill in).

Beat the cream cheese with the sugar and heavy cream until very creamy with an electric mixer. Fill pan with layer of cream cheese mixture and a layer of ladyfingers. Repeat until full. Top with your favorite topping and refrigerate. (Any leftover ladyfingers and mixture, make sandwiches and refrigerate.)

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Melt butter and mix milk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake in pie shell at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes or until thick, use knife to test.
Beat egg with 1/4 cup sugar for topping.

title: chickpea tahini-hummus *
directions: Drain the chickpeas but save the liquid.
Put the chickpeas, 2 tablespoons packing liquid, lemon juice, garlic and salt in food processor and puree.
Add a small amount of additional packing liquid to facilitate blending together.
Add the sesame tahini and blend it into the chickpea mixture.
Serve with pita bread or raw vegetables.

title: sausage and zucchini
directions: After Italian sausage has been browned well and sliced, add onions
to
sausage
drippings and brown lightly (judge if too much grease,
if
you
have
too much pour some off).
Add sausage slices, tomatoes, zucchini, lemon juice, oregano, salt and hot red pepper sauce.
Stir-fry for 5 minutes only.
Enjoy plain or
with freshly
grated Parmesan cheese, sprinkled.
I always serve this over white rice and add a fresh green salad and French or Italian bread for a delightful meal.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cover cabbage with water and add salt.
Bring to boil only. Drain well.
Put in casserole.
Add 1 can cream of celery soup. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour until brown.

title: spring fruit pie
directions: Mix fruit, sugar, rind and tapioca and let stand while preparing pastry for 2-crust pie.
Use strips across top of pie. Bake in 450° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hot dog potato casserole
directions: Mix together garlic, salt, pepper and nutmeg; set aside.
Peel and thinly slice potatoes.
Add 3 tablespoons flour to shredded cheese.
Layer in greased pan: hot dogs, cheese, onion, milk, oleo and dry ingredients; then potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Pour heavy cream on top after baking.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: grandma's chicken and dumplings
directions: You will need a big pan with cover.

title: party mix con queso
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In open roasting pan, melt margarine. Stir in seasoning mix.
Gradually add cereal, chips and crackers. Stir to coat.
Bake 15 minutes; stir.
Bake 15 more minutes.
Add Parmesan and stir again.
Bake 15 more minutes.
Cool on paper towel.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick butter; set aside.
Mix potatoes, onion and Cheddar.
Mix butter, soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and stir.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and mix with corn flakes.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour until potatoes are tender.

title: broccoli casserole
