directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt the margarine in casserole dish.
Add rice, water, the broccoli, celery and onion.
Combine the soup with water; pour over top.
Spread grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage; mix with salt and let stand 1 hour.
Add carrot and green pepper.
Combine vinegar, water, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed; boil 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm; pour over slaw. Put into containers and freeze.
Slaw will thaw in a short time. Can be refrozen.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mash avocados in bowl; add lemon juice, salt and pepper and mix well.
Blend sour cream with mayonnaise and taco seasoning in small bowl.
Spread refried beans in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer avocado mixture, sour cream mix and green onion and olives over beans.
Chill until ready to serve.
Add tomatoes and cheese just before serving.

title: taco sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in refrigerator.
The flavor of this sauce improves with age.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Layer in Pyrex dish:
First hamburger, refried beans, salsa mixed with sour cream and grated cheese sprinkled on top.
Put in oven at 325° for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with taco chips.
Serves about 20 to 30 people.

title: feather bed rolls
directions: Crumble yeast into bowl; add milk.
Gradually add sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening or butter.
Stir in flour alternately with yeast mixture, beating after each addition.
Beat until dough is smooth and well blended.
Scrape dough from sides of bowl. Cover with damp cloth; let rise in warm place for 1 hour.
Punch down with spoon.
Drop by teaspoons into lightly greased pans. Cover with damp cloth, let rise 20 minutes or double in size. Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: fried zucchini
directions: Mix egg, milk, flour, salt and garlic powder to form batter. Dip zucchini until well coated.
Fry in hot oil until golden.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Brown onion flakes in butter or margarine.
Roll chicken pieces in flour. When onion pieces are tender, place chicken in frypan and cook until golden brown.
Remove chicken from pan.
Add 2 tablespoons more of butter or margarine; add brown sugar. When sugar is dissolved, add pineapple juice and half of cherry
juice. Cook at medium heat until mixture boils.
Add cooked chicken and simmer 15 minutes. Add all of pineapple and cherries (not cherry juice); simmer 15 minutes longer and serve. Serves 4.

title: mini cheesecake tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream first 4 ingredients well with mixer.
Place a wafer in foil baking cup.
Fill each cup 3/4 full of batter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with your favorite pie filling (cherry, blueberry, etc.) when done.

title: six weeks muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt in large bowl. Add eggs, shortening and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Store in covered container in refrigerator to use as needed.

Keeps up to 6 weeks. Fill muffin tins that have been coated with shortening 2/3 full. Bake in preheated oven at 375° to 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 5 dozen muffins depending on size of muffin tin.

title: baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon from skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook onions in bacon drippings until tender.
Stir in pork and beans, brown sugar, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Stir in bacon.
Let stand before serving.

title: frozen cranberry banana salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into medium bowl.
Set pineapple aside. Add bananas to the juice.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: Chop the sausage coarsely
by hand or a food processor. Transfer the sausage and onion to a deep pan and saute over medium heat until the sausage is lightly browned, about 8 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spinach pies(fathiyir bi spanegh)
directions: Squeeze chopped spinach to remove all water.
Add chopped parsley, nuts, seasonings, salt, lemon, oil and mint.
Mix very well.
Roll ball of dough into circle and add heaping tablespoonful of filling and close in triangular shape.
Place on oiled cookie sheet at 400° for about 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crackers, and pour into baking dish.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Take out of oven and top with crackers.
Place back in oven and bake for 20 to 25 minutes more or until bubbly and crackers are lightly brown.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion together; add taco seasoning.
Add all other ingredients.
May be put in crock-pot for an hour or two. Garnish with grated cheese and tortilla chips.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Add lemon rind to butter and cream well.
Add sugar gradually, blending after each addition.
Add egg yolks and beat thoroughly. Add lemon juice, flour, Grape-Nuts and milk, mixing well.
Fold in egg whites.
Turn into greased 8-inch baking dish and place in pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Check after 1 hour.
When done, it has a crust on top with the pudding below.
Serve hot or cold with cream.
Serves 6.

title: pink frozen salad
directions: Mix all together in order as listed.
Spoon into 2 1/2-quart container.
Mold and freeze.
Unmold to serve.

title: lemon bread
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients; add wheat germ.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine water and lemon juice; add to shortening, sugar and egg mixture with lemon peel.
Pour into flour mixture; stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Do not beat.
Turn into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until it tests done.

title: barbecued beef patties
directions: Add to meat and cook slowly approximately 20 minutes.
Blend in 1 tablespoon flour.

title: chocolate covered cherry cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pudding mix.
Add eggs, oil and water; beat well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Cook at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together flour, Crisco and salt.
Add ice water and stir with fork.
Roll out for pies on floured surface.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pie shells.

title: monterey casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain. Add onion, salt and tomato sauce. Simmer on low heat for 5 to 10 minutes. Place 3 cups Fritos in 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese on top. Pour meat sauce over chips and cheese. Top with remaining Fritos and cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. When serving, add lettuce, tomatoes and olives as toppings.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Combine all liquid ingredients.
(Note: Melt shortening before measuring.) Make well in dry ingredients.
Pour in all liquid ingredients at once into well.
Mix together.
Batter can be stored in a covered container in the refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
When ready to bake, fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: brownie drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: souper burger italiano
directions: Brown ground beef, chopped onion and oregano.
Add minestrone soup, catsup and water.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Spread on toasted buns.
Place strips of cheese on each.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: my mother's rolls
directions: Heat milk, shortening and sugar until milk is scalded.
Cool. When mixture is cool, add yeast dissolved in lukewarm water, mix in 4 cups of flour and set in a warm place to rise.
When double in bulk, work down.
Add remaining flour, salt, baking powder and soda, sifted together.
The rolls will be easier to make out if this mixture is put in refrigerator and allowed to get cold.
Make out rolls and dip in melted butter or margarine.
Let rise and bake at 350° until brown.

title: chicken cordon bleu roll-ups
directions: In glass baking dish, melt butter; set aside.
Between 2 pieces of plastic wrap, lightly pound chicken to flatten for even cooking.
Place 1 slice of ham and cheese on each breast; start at narrow end and lightly roll up.
Roll in flour, then in melted butter, then in stuffing mix.
Place in baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican beef kabobs
directions: Combine water and vinegar in jar with tight-fitting lid.
Add salad dressing mix and chili powder.
Shake well.
Add oil and fruit juice and shake again.
Pour over meat cubes in glass bowl. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drain and reserve marinade. Place meat and vegetables on 4 long skewers.
Broil in preheated broiler or over glowing coals for 4 to 5 minutes on each side, brushing frequently with reserved marinade.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add the remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Serve with crackers.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill.
Garnish just before serving.

title: egg, cheese and ham omelette
directions: Beat all together.
Pour into omelette pan that has been greased with butter.
Cook on low to medium until egg is cooked through and cheese is melted through.
Salt and pepper to taste. Serve with toast and choice of jam.

title: coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Line bottom of pan with cherries and nuts.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag.
Melt brown sugar and margarine.
Add half of the biscuits to cinnamon mixture and shake.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni for 12 minutes in salted water; drain.
Mix macaroni, peas, tuna and soup together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese and melted butter.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix together and top with maraschino cherries.
May add 1 cup raisins.

title: stir-fried pork with vegetables(amounts are for 4 servings.)
directions: Cut meat into 1/2 to 3/4-inch cubes, removing any fatty parts. Set aside.
Partially thaw the green beans.
Add onions and peppers to butter in heavy, large skillet.
Saute for 1 minute. Ad meat and green beans and stir-fry over high heat until all pieces are heated through.
Add salt, paprika and black pepper. Mix well.
Pour in the beef or chicken broth.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain liquid from all beans except kidney beans.
Combine all ingredients.
Thoroughly mix oil, vinegar and sugar and pour over salad.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Stir a few times to completely coat beans.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into muffin pans lined with cupcake liners.
Freeze.
Remove just before serving.
Yields 18 to 24.

title: lime party salad
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk in top of double boiler.
Pour hot mixture over package of jello. Stir until dissolved.
Mix in cream cheese. Blend until cheese dissolves. Add pineapple.
Cool. Blend in whipped cream and mayonnaise.
Chill until firm.
This is great with orange jello, also.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If too thick, add some pineapple juice.

title: barley pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients except fruit flavored yogurt.
Pour into a 6 cup casserole with a tight fitting lid.
Bake for about 2 hours.
Milk should be absorbed and barley soft.
Serve warm, topped with flavored yogurt.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice off peaches and mix with instant pudding mix.
Mix all fruit and stir in pudding mix. Refrigerate.

title: perfect cornbread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in cornmeal.
Add eggs, milk and shortening.
Beat with electric mixer until just smooth, about 1 minute.
Pour batter into greased 9x9x2-inch pan.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 20-25 minutes.

title: pat's pizza
directions: Cook sausage, ground beef, onions and peppers; drain well. Mix pizza crust mix with water and stir until blended.
Form into a ball; cover and set in a warm place for 5 minutes.
With greased fingers, press dough evenly onto a greased pan.
For a chewy crust:
bake lightly for 3 to 4 minutes.
Mix spices with tomato sauce and spoon over crust.
Top with meats, mushrooms and cheese. Bake at 500° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts and begins to brown.
Warning:
This makes a really thick and gooey pizza; forks needed!

title: easy one dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, ham and onion powder in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix Bisquick and 1 1/2 cups milk in a bowl and pour evenly over mixture in dish.
Bake for 27 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Let set 5 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese crispies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Stir by hand until well blended.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap and chill 30 minutes.

title: souper quick and easy stroganoff
directions: Brown the beef in a heavy skillet. Drain any excess grease. Combine the mushroom soup, onion dip, and water.
Mix well and add to the skillet along with the cooked noodles.
Stir and keep warm until serving time.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetables with fish(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle fish with approximately 3 tablespoons chicken soup.
Roll up fish and place in baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Sprinkle remaining chicken soup, pepper and paprika over fish.
Place vegetables around fish. Cover and bake for 55 minutes.
(May be microwaved on High for 20 minutes.)

title: chicago crunchy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugars, egg, milk and vanilla in bowl until blended.
Stir in flour, soda and salt alternately with oil until mixture is thoroughly mixed.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and walnuts.

title: bill's favorite cheesecake
directions: Follow the order of the recipe, mixing well after each is added at medium speed.
Bake in spring pan at 350° for 1 hour. Turn off oven and leave in oven for 1 hour longer.
Leave plain or top with favorite fruit.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Cook sausage in skillet until browned; drain.
Remove from heat.
Stir in next 7 ingredients, mixing well.
Place mixture in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour water over top. Cover and bake at 350° for one hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Combine meat and soup.
Pour into a 13 x 9 casserole dish, alternating meat mixture and cheese (save 1 cup of cheese for later).
Cover top completely with tater tots.
Bake at 350 degrees until tots are golden brown.
Then take remaining cup of cheese and sprinkle on tots and return to oven until cheese melts. Serve hot.
May divide recipe in half for smaller families.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: streamlined cassoulet
directions: In a 5 to 6-quart pan over high heat, combine onion, carrots, bell pepper, garlic and 1/2 cup water.
Stir often until browned bits stick in pan.
Add another 1/2 cup water. Scrape browned bits free and boil until vegetables begin to brown. Repeat 1 or 2 more times, until vegetables are richly browned.
Add tomatoes, broth, wine, thyme, bay leaf, pepper and liquid pepper. Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes to blend flavors.
Add beans and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Add chicken and sausage. Simmer gently until chicken pieces are white in the center (cut to test), about 10 minutes. Ladle into bowls; add salt to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: "45" minute chicken
directions: Place the chicken in electric skillet.
Add the cola, ketchup and barbecue sauce.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball ii
directions: Soften cheeses
for
several
hours.
Mix at low speed on mixer. Add mayonnaise and
the rest of the ingredients.
This makes 2 large or 3 medium-sized balls.
Roll in nuts and refrigerate.

title: pepper steak and rice
directions: Brown beef strips slowly in 1 tsp. oil or shortening.
Add garlic salt, pepper and soy sauce.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes more.
Add green peppers and onion.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes until green peppers are tender.
Add a little water if needed.
Keep covered, then add tomatoes.
Stirring uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes more, or until thick and rich.
Serve over rice.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together; beat until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs and milk; beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; add to mixture.
Shape into mound; wrap in waxed paper and chill thoroughly.
Roll on board lightly floured with confectioners sugar, until dough is about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut cookies, then place on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.

title: chocolate coconut souffle
directions: Beat cream cheese and milk with beater in saucepan.
Add chocolate chips.
Heat over low heat.
Stir until chocolate chips melt.
Beat egg yolks and salt together.
Stir part of chocolate mixture into egg yolks.
Stir egg yolks into rest of chocolate mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until slightly thickened.
Stir in coconut and vanilla.
Cool.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli in a 9 x 9-inch greased pan, cooked boned chicken on top.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise and lemon.
Pour sauce on top of chicken and broccoli.
Crumble bread and mix with cheese and butter.
Top the casserole with crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can also substitute ham.

title: spur of the moment bran muffins
directions: Make this mix ahead of time and have it on hand in the refrigerator for whenever you have a craving for a bran muffin.

title: shrimp mold for crackers
directions: Heat soup, gelatin and salt to boiling, then take off heat. Add mayonnaise and cream cheese; mix all together with whisk. Stir in celery, onion and shrimp.
Mold and chill until firm. Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: hazelnut chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Mix together chocolate
chips, vanilla wafers, hazelnuts, sugar and butter.
Mix well. Press into bottom and up sides of greased 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix together. Grease and flour pans. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: potato kugellettes
directions: Grate potatoes, add egg whites, pepper, pepper sauce and baking powder.
Using nonstick muffin pan, add 1/3 cup mixture to each cup.
Place in 400° oven and bake 20 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake until lightly browned, around 20 minutes.
Total recipe 413 calories.

title: broccoli-mushroom medley
directions: Steam broccoli for 1 to 2 minutes or until crisp-tender. Rinse in cold water and set aside.
In a bowl, combine lemon juice, salt, sugar, cornstarch and nutmeg.
Set aside.
In a large skillet or wok over high heat, stir-fry mushrooms, onion and garlic in oil for 3 minutes.
Add broccoli and lemon juice mixture.
Stir-fry for 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: dandy sweet potatoes
directions: Drain the sweet potatoes and arrange them in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Add the remaining ingredients. Bake, covered, for 40 minutes in a 350° oven, basting occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into balls the size of a quarter.
Bake at 400° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: green bean and tomato salad with mozzarella
directions: Cook beans until crisp-tender. Drain well. Toss with remaining ingredients and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
May be served chilled or at room temperature.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: appetizer tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese, chilies, salt, olives, cheese, onions and garlic powder.
Use this as a filling.
Divide the filling and spread evenly over tortillas.
Roll up and cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate several hours.
Unwrap and cut into 1/2-inch slices (electric knife works well).
Discard ends.
Place pinwheels around on plate, leaving space for bowl of salsa in center.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes about 50 pinwheels.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix flour and shortening as for biscuits.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Place in large mixing bowl and place in refrigerator.
Use as needed.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Heat the butter and oil in a deep skillet or saute pan over medium heat.
When the butter foam begins to subside, add the garlic and chicken quarters, skin side down or skinless.
When the chicken is well browned on one side, turn pieces over and add the rosemary.
If the garlic starts to blacken, remove it.
If however, the garlic turns deep brown, leave it until the chicken is cooked. Control the heat so that the oil stays hot but doesn't burn anything.
When you have browned the chicken well on all sides, add a large pinch of salt, pepper and the wine.
Allow the wine to bubble rapidly for 2 to 3 minutes.
Lower heat to simmer and cover the pan.
Cook slowly until the chicken is tender to prick with a fork.
Turn the chicken 2 or 3 times while cooking.
If the cooking liquid begins to dry up, add 2 or more tablespoons water as needed. Transfer the chicken to a warm serving platter, removing most of the cooking fat from pan.
Add water to taste and scrape bottom of pan to mix in the cooking juices thoroughly.
Pour this over the chicken or make a gravy-like mixture to serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: mrs. debbie's grits casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Press dough out evenly in a 10 to 12-inch pizza pan or pie pan.
Starting from the center outward, lay apple slices in concentric circles, each overlapping.
Place in the oven; bake 10 minutes.
While baking, heat preserves in a small saucepan on medium heat until melted enough to coat a spoon.

title: icebox cake
directions: Mix
this
all together and press in graham cracker box lined with aluminum foil.
Keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: white chili
directions: Dump all of this in a crockpot.
Cook for three hours on high.
Delicious

title: easy apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients; cook for 15 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: grilled zucchini squash
directions: Wash squash and zucchini.
Cut off ends and discard.
Cut into slices (the short way, like discs) about 1/2-inch - 3/4-inch thick.
Score the slices front and back.
Marinate the slices in Italian dressing for at least 3 hours, periodically shaking it up. Grill on low temperature setting until tender - turning once (it should take about 30 minutes to grill).

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Combine mayonnaise and sour cream.
Crumble and stir in cheese.
Cut celery into sticks.
Chop onion and mince garlic. Cook onion in oil over medium heat until soft, about 2 minutes. Add garlic; cook 1 minute.
Squeeze in juice of lemon.
Stir in tomato sauce, Tabasco and salt.
Cook for 5 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Combine brown sugar, flour, oatmeal and cinnamon.
Cut butter into mixture until crumbly.
Press mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: chicken broccoli for a banquet
directions: Mix together and put in buttered baking dishes, cake type pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° (325° in glass pan).
Cover with cheese slices or shredded cheese.
Makes 2 (9 x 13-inch) dishes.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans, well.
Chill.
Shape into ball.
Roll in pecans.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt the butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together 1 cup sugar, flour and milk and pour over the melted butter.
Heat to boiling 1 cup sugar and the fruit and pour over the batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy fettucini
directions: Prepare fettucini by directions; drain.
While noodles are cooking, cook and stir garlic in oil on low heat in skillet until golden brown.
Stir in cheese spread, milk and Parmesan cheese. Stir until melted thoroughly and add fettucini noodles.
Stir lightly.
Serve immediately.

title: quick carbonara(italian ham spaghetti)
directions: Brown bacon; drain, crumble and reserve.
In electric frypan or large skillet, saute lightly the oil, butter, garlic and ham. Add cooked spaghetti, bacon, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper; stir well.
Turn off heat.
Pour beaten eggs over and quickly toss to coat spaghetti evenly.
Add olives and pimentos, if desired. Serve at once.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: pink party punch
directions: Have pineapple grapefruit drink and ginger ale well chilled. Pour into a punch bowl.
Float scoops of strawberry ice cream on top.
Add sliced strawberries.

title: think thin coffee milk shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high for 15 seconds.
Tastes like the real thing, but boasts only 85 calories.

title: peanut butter unbaked cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar, peanut butter and butter or margarine. Add dates, nuts and coconut; mix together.
Make patties and chill.

title: italian sausage bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Cook sausage until it is no longer pink, crumbling it as you cook. Unroll one pack of dough and roll it to a 10 x 12-inch rectangle. Spread 1/2 pizza sauce over dough, leaving a 1-inch edge. Mix sausage, cheese and olives together and spread 1/2 of mixture over sauce. Starting at the longest side, roll dough up tightly, pinching seam to seal. Place on baking stone. Follow same instructions for second dough. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: May use pumpkin that already has spices in it.
Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes (mixture will be thick).

title: chicken in oven (or pork chops)
directions: Salt, pepper and flour chicken as for frying and place in a greased oblong pan or dish.
Bake at 350° until brown, then add either the mushroom sauce, celery soup or water.
Add enough water to mix well.
Place back in oven, reduce heat, cover and bake for 45 minutes, until done and tender.

title: patchwork relish
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; sprinkle with salt.
Cover and let stand at room temperature overnight.
Drain; cover vegetables with vinegar in a kettle.
Add sugar, mustard and celery seed.
Boil 1 hour.
Add turmeric and mix well.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: betty's moist pound cake
directions: Note:
Do not use salt, soda or baking powder.

title: christmas punch
directions: Float strawberries on top.

title: yum yum cake(serves 15)
directions: Make cake as per package instructions for high altitude.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Leave in pan and cool.
Poke holes in cake with a fork.
Combine crushed pineapple and brown sugar. Bring to a boil.
Cool slightly and spoon over cooled cake.
Let seep in.
Then let cool.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix together. Cook at 325° for 1 hour.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: pickled eggs
directions: Place eggs and small beets in large glass jar.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Heat (do not boil).
Pour into jar over eggs and beets.
Cool, cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels (not too fine).
Mix with butter or margarine and brown sugar.
Pack into large 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
(This is the crust or base.)

title: delicious rolls
directions: Mix
well.
Spray muffin pans with Pam.
Fill about 3/4 full. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: lemon fish
directions: Place butter in baking dish.
Microwave on High to melt butter (45 seconds).
Blend in seasonings.
Coat fish fillets in mixture. Place around in dish.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High until fish flakes (with fork).
Approximate time is 5 to 6 minutes.

title: coq au vin
directions: Brown chicken in butter and bacon.
Add onion.
Drain off some fat.
Push aside in pan and add seasonings.
Add sherry and simmer 45 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Add mushrooms and flour (if you like thick gravy) and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour gravy over chicken (and rice, too!).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: best punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil.
Remove from heat; add jello. Mix until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over crushed ice and let stand 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese shrimp dip
directions: Stir milk, 1 tablespoon at a time into cream cheese.
Blend mayonnaise, onions, horseradish, pepper sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in shrimp.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate for at least one hour.
Makes 2 1/2 cups dip.

title: pecan butter balls
directions: Cream butter.
Add honey, then add flour, salt and vanilla. Mix well and add chopped nuts.
Form into about 1-inch balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes in a 300° oven.
Roll in powdered sugar while still hot, then roll in sugar again after they are cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: drop chicken 'n' dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in water. Remove from broth and take off bones. Return chicken to broth.
Add 2 cups milk, margarine, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Heat fruit.
Mix sugar with flour.
Beat egg and add milk, sugar and flour.
Melt butter.
Mix together and pour over top of hot fruit which has been peeled and quartered.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: delicious pickle recipe
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions, peppers and whole garlic cloves.
Add salt.
Cover with cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumber mixture.
Heat to boiling.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.

title: cajun black beans and rice
directions: Drain water from soaked beans; cover with water equal to 3 times volume of beans. Add oil and bring to boil. Turn down heat and simmer 1 hour. Add rice (and water if necessary).
Rice needs 3 cups water to absorb. Bring to boil, then simmer 1 hour. Add all remaining ingredients. Cook 10 to 15 minutes on low.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; set aside.
In separate bowl, beat eggs and mushroom soup (optional can of mushrooms).
Add onion; mix well.
Add mayonnaise.
Put into bottom of casserole dish and layer of broccoli, grated cheese and mushroom soup mixture. Continue to layer until gone.
Scatter croutons on top.
Melt stick of margarine and spoon over top of croutons.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Into a heavy iron skillet, measure white sugar and butter. Cook over high heat until lightly browned.
Stir to prevent burning.
Add milk to mixture slowly and cook slowly until slightly thickened.
Beat until smooth.
While still not thick enough to hold shape, smooth 1 tablespoon of icing on each layer. This will soak in and make cake hold moisture.
When remainder of icing has been beaten enough to hold shape, smooth between layers, top and sides.

title: cheddar cheese cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well (except for pecans).
Chill well, then roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheets and flatten. Add pecan half if desired.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Can be served hot or cold.
Can be served at parties, tastes similar to cheese straws.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except eggs and cheese.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Fold in eggs.
Serve on lettuce leaves and garnish with grated cheese.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in the order given.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix juices and sugar.
Pour into punch bowl over ice.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.

title: lila's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Add milk; beat well.
Add baking powder and flour.
Blend well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Check for doneness with broom straw or toothpick.
Use well greased and floured ring pan.
Cool 1/2 hour before removing from pan.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Serve.

title: stuffed jalapeno peppers
directions: Mix potted meat, pickle relish, mayonnaise and enough cracker crumbs to make a thick meat paste.
Cut the tips off peppers; remove seeds and membrane.
Fill peppers with mixture.
Serve as hors d'oeuvres.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Cook carrots 5 to 7 minutes, until crisp-tender.
Cook celery 5 minutes only.
Mix with other vegetables.
Pour soup and rest of ingredients over the vegetables.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: To make crust mix first 3 ingredients together, and press into a 9x13-inch pan.
To make filling mix pudding according to directions on box, with milk.
Then add Cool Whip.
Crush 4-5 large Butterfingers, add to pudding mixture.
Pour over crust and refrigerate.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix hamburger, rice, 1/2 cup water, then onion, salt, celery salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls.
Cook meatballs in skillet until brown on all sides; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over meatballs.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add water during cooking, if necessary.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Add bread to egg mixture.
Brown sausage and add to egg mixture. Add cheese and mix.
Chill overnight and bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Spread mayonnaise on both sides of chicken.
Put bread in food processor and make into crumbs; not too small.
Put on a plate. Roll chicken into crumbs, put on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam. Grate Parmesan cheese over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 hour. Thinner chicken takes less time.

title: sugar-free chocolate sauce
directions: Heat fructose, cornstarch and 1/3 cup water in saucepan until thick.
To this mixture, add vanilla, margarine and cocoa; stir well and add enough hot water, 1 tablespoon at a time, until you reach a spreadable consistency.
Pour on top of cake and let drizzle down sides.

title: mary odom's chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening. Add sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add vanilla to milk.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: anisette cookies
directions: Put all dry ingredients into a large bowl. Add stick of butter.
Into a smaller bowl, put eggs, anise flavor and anise seeds.
Beat well.
Make a well in the middle of the dry ingredients. Add the egg mixture; mix all together.
Add a small amount of flour, if necessary, to keep dough from being too sticky.
Flour board.
Turn dough out and pat with hand to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into three 3-inch strips and put onto baking sheet.
Bake until golden brown in 350° oven.

Remove from oven and cut into diagonal strips about 1-inch wide. Return to sheet, placing them first on one side for approximately 5 minutes, then turning to the other for 5 minutes, toasting them until golden.
Watch carefully.
Will keep several weeks if covered tightly.

title: pie crust(makes 6 pie crusts)
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in 1-cup container.
Mix together until well blended.
Add the flour and shortening gradually until blended.
Makes 6 pie crusts.
Freeze in ball in bag until ready to use. Roll out.

title: rich pear custard
directions: *Whip chopped, fresh or canned pears in a blender or processor.

title: sweet peas
directions: Put oil and flour in pot to make roux; brown roux, then add chopped onions and cook until clear. Add peas with water to pot. In each can, fill 3/4 way with water and 1 teaspoon sugar and stir well, then add to pot. When gravy starts to get thick, add potatoes and lower the fire. You might have to add a little more water to finish potatoes. Serve over hot rice.

title: aunt rita's meatballs
directions: Mix all and make into meatballs on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: apple delight
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Put in ungreased 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole dish.
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Mix in butter. Shape into a crust and place on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Excellent as a side dish or a dessert.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in hot fruit juices (1/2 cherry and 1/2 pineapple) totaling 1 cup.
Add Coke and drained fruit.
(Mix cream cheese in food processor with cooled Jello mixture, cool down with Coke.)
Put in small ring mold in refrigerator until set.
(Note: This is for small ring mold.
If using large mold, which serves 18-20 people, double the recipe except for the bing cherries.)

title: buttermilk chocolate cake
directions: Just
before starting to mix cake, pour 2/3 cup boiling water into unsweetened chocolate and melt.
Mix well and cool.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in blueberries.
Add milk, egg and butter.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
The batter will be lumpy.
Do not overbeat.
Spoon batter in twelve 2 1/2-inch greased muffin cups. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Serve warm.

title: snacking cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as package directs.
Add sugar and bananas. Mix well.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Cook at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an unbaked crust. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for another 30 minutes. Yummy!!

title: lazanki(noodles to go with soups)
directions: Sift flour; add pinch of salt and knead with egg and water. Roll out fine; set aside to dry.
Cut the dried dough.
Toss lightly on floured board after cutting.
Cook lazanki in boiling salted water; drain and pour over with hot water.
Drain.
Then when Czarnina is done, place the cooked lazanki
in.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in greased baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic, parsley and black pepper in olive oil over medium heat for a few minutes.
Stir often and do not let garlic get brown.
Next, add 2 cans of clams (and the juice from the cans) plus the bottle of additional clam juice.
Stir together and bring mixture to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: paw-pau's macaroni pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Layer spaghetti, cheese, salt and pepper in 9 x 12-inch oblong dish.
Heat milk and butter on low until butter melts.
Do not boil.
Pour over dish and put crust on. Fold under edges to make oblong crust.
Fold in center.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until crust browns.

title: b~b~q brisket
directions: Mix all ingredients except for brisket.
Rub mixture on both sides of brisket; refrigerate over night covered with foil.
Bake at 350 degrees for three and half to four hours with foil covering.

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Cream together brown sugar, shortening and egg until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream; mix well after each addition.	Stir in rhubarb.
Spoon into well-greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan. Sprinkle batter with topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tests done.
Serve warm or cool.
Serves 12-15.

title: ice cream sundae
directions: Place ice cream in a small bowl.
Drizzle caramel or chocolate syrup over ice cream and add whipped cream and nuts.
Top off with the cherry.

title: curry or chili cheese logs
directions: Cream the cream cheese and garlic together until blended; mix in the chopped nuts.
Shape into two logs, each about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Roll in curry or chili powder which you've sprinkled on wax paper.
Wrap each roll in waxed paper or clear plastic film and chill.
Slice into rounds 1/8-inch thick and serve with thin crisp crackers.
Try one roll of each.
Makes about 150 appetizers.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Wash chicken well.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Rub a little liquid smoke on each piece.
Place on greased broiler pan, skin side down.
Broil at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Turn, skin side up, and broil for another 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and brush with barbecue sauce.

title: apple pear coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches. Cream 1/2 cup butter and the granular sugar.
Mix in eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt alternately with sour cream.
Fold in apples and pears.

title: julie's sweet 'n sour meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and form meatballs.
Brown in shortening.
Pour off fat.

title: chicken asparagus soup
directions: In saucepan, blend soups. Gradually stir in milk. Heat to serving temperature, stirring occasionally. Garnish with parsley.
